title: butternut (or hubbard) squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: southern pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown seasoned pork chops; put in a shallow baking dish. Dissolve cubes in water; pour over chops.
Add rice, green pepper and onion.
Put tomato on top just long enough to cook.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix together beans, peas, onion and pimento.
Mix together sugar and vinegar.
Pour over the rest of ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	(will be a moist ball). Put apples
in	greased
9-inch
pie dish.
Top with dough and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine bread cubes, chopped onion and pepper, egg and ground beef together, turning lightly with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Do not stir more than necessary as it tends to make the loaf tough.
Shape into an oval loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge with peanut butter
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Add milk; stir well.
Cook on low to medium heat until boiled, then cook for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from stove.
Add peanut butter; stir until it gets firmer, then spread on platter.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and cook cornbread mix.
Cool and crumble.
Add diced tomatoes and chopped pepper and onion.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.
Keep refrigerated.
Will keep up to 1 week.

title: venison stew
directions: Cut meat in small pieces.
Dredge in flour.
Melt butter and brown meat.
Add mushrooms, onions, pepper and celery.
Add beef stock to cover meat and vegetables.
Simmer 2 hours.
Then add wine, potatoes, carrots and corn.
Cook 30 minutes more.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Mix the ingredients, except for noodles, all together.
Bake at 325° (covered) for 3 hours.
Cook noodles and add to the mixture until of desired consistency.

title: ham & potato breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into an ungreased 13x9-inch pan.
Bake uncovered until knife comes out clean when inserted, about 60-70 minutes.

title: one pan chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Put cup of rice in middle of pan.
Pour cans of onion and mushroom soups over rice.
Salt and butter chicken, if desired.

title: mexican stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients except Hamburger Helper.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add macaroni and sauce mix from Hamburger Helper.
Simmer 15 minutes. This is juicy when served first, but macaroni absorbs juice after standing.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 1/2 packages cookie dough in bottom of pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer. Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips in cream cheese mixture.
Spread over cookie dough.
Slice other half of cookie dough and put on top. Bake at 350° or until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well and mix with softened cream cheese, pepper, onion and salt; stir in half the nuts.
Make a ball.
Roll ball in remaining nuts and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: fish florentine
directions: Arrange fillets in bottom of shallow baking dish. Cover fish with well drained spinach. Combine crackers, cheese and wheat germ (if used). Pour over fish and spinach.
Bake, uncovered at 400° for 15-20 Min.
Serves 4.

title: chicken eden isle
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with dried beef.
Roll chicken breast in ball with bacon wrapped around it, use toothpick to hold. Mix with mixer:
sour cream, cream cheese and soup; then pour over the top of chicken and bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice.
Sauce will thicken a little. Makes 4 servings or can be doubled for more servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oats and boiling water and sit aside.
Mix flour with sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
When mixed, add butter, oats mixture and vanilla.
Beat until mixed 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls the size of a nickel.
Flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown in a 350° oven. Makes 5 dozen.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well except bell pepper.
Use bell pepper on top of salad to garnish.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well. Bake 20 minutes or until bubbly and brown on edges.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Combine all ingredients; stir.
Serve in fondue pot for dip with Fritos or serve over cooked rice for vegetable dish.

title: deep fried camembert
directions: Cut each Camambert round into 6 wedges.
In a bowl combine bread crumbs and sesame seeds.
Dip each wedge in beaten egg and then bread crumb mixture.
Finish all of the wedges.
Heat 2 inches of oil in pan on medium high heat.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Serve on a toothpick with some juicy strawberries.

title: texas taters
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; toss well to mix.
Pour mixture into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat cake mix, oil, sugar, eggs and sour cream together and pour into a well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon, pecans and raisins together.
Sprinkle over top of cake batter.
With a spoon handle, swirl topping into cake.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Combine sugar and melted margarine.
Add enough warm milk to make a thin glaze.
Pour over warm cake.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables halfway according to package directions.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover with American cheese slices.
Spread crackers and oleo mixture over cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rum syrup
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm; add lemon juice and rum.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (1 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in orange juice and peel until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups. Bake 20 minutes.

title: cookies and cream parfaits
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is completely dissolved (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm (about 1 minute).

title: spring fling
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Pour into glasses.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: country style tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time; beat well.
Add part of the combined flour, baking soda and cream of tartar, alternating with milk until all is used.
Beat well after each addition.
Roll thin and cut with cookie cutter into desired shape.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: argentine caramel
directions: Mix ingredients together in a double boiler and cook on stove top for 30 minutes.

title: dietetic milkshake
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender and blend until milkshake foams up and ice cube disappears.

title: doris' ultimate southern pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat eggs (not too stiff) and slowly pour the hot syrup into the eggs.
Add butter, vanilla and pecan meats.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes, or until set.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir mayonnaise, vinegar, mustard, sugar, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add macaroni, celery, green pepper and onion.
Toss to coat well.
Chill and cover.
Makes 5 cups.

title: string pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and brown the ground beef.
Drain the beef and add the sauce.
Drain spaghetti.
Mix spaghetti with the eggs, butter and Parmesan cheese.
Layer the spaghetti in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next spread the 8 ounces of cottage cheese on spaghetti, next add the meat mixture and then the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Note:
Only rinse out cans, do not add water to soup.

title: western dip
directions: Brown beef. Drain; put in slow cooker. Add chili and cheese cut in small pieces. Chop tamales in small pieces. Add to mixture. Cook until cheese is melted. Can be served hot with chips. This makes a large amount of dip.

title: bratten's clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables; add enough water to barely cover and simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Then melt butter; add flour and blend.
Cook 1 or 2 minutes; add half and half and cook, stirring, until smooth and thick.
Add undrained vegetables and clams; heat through.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.

title: chicken and potato casserole
directions: Grease square baking dish.
Layer the potatoes, then chicken, then onion.
Combine the soup and milk.
Pour over the chicken. Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake another 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Make night before.
Spray Pam on dish (8 x 8-inch or similar size).
Break bread in small pieces and lay on bottom of dish. Layer sausage on bread.
Layer cheese.
On the side, mix milk and eggs.
Pour milk and eggs mixture over casserole.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in the morning.

title: herbed tomatoes(may prepare ahead.  serves 6.)
directions: Put tomatoes in a bowl.
Shake together remaining ingredients in a jar; pour over tomatoes and let marinate for at least 1 hour.

title: pear jam
directions: Peel pears and core.
Put through food chopper.
Mix ingredients and boil until thick and clear.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Cut fryer into parts; wash and drain.
Add seasoned salt, hot sauce, black pepper and red pepper.
Batter chicken in flour mixture.
Drop pieces into hot Crisco oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix wafer crumbs, nuts and sugar.
Pour in orange juice and butter, stir.
Roll in coconut and powdered sugar.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bones.
Add corn, lima beans and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add the eggs when done.

title: purple cow
directions: Combine grape juice, ice cream and yogurt in an electric blender container; cover.
Whirl until smooth.
Pour into 2 tall glasses.
Serve immediately.
Garnish with grapes.

title: red and green cabbage salad
directions: Shred small heads of cabbage.
Mix all the ingredients (except the cabbage) in a jar.
Shake well and pour over shredded cabbage. Let set for 2 hours, then serve.

title: lou jean's cheese cake tarts
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Place muffin liners in tins.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each tin liner.
Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Let cool. Top with fresh fruit or the filling of your choice. Chill.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Measure flour out and add baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Sift again.
Add chopped nuts.
Mix well and set aside.
Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time, mixing well.
Stir in white chocolate chips. Spread in a 9 X 9 X 2 inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean or with slightly fudgy looking crumbs.
Serve blondies warmed so they will be soft with ice cream and maple butter sauce, the recipe of which follows.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add vinegar and salt.
Let cool. Then fold in remaining ingredients.
Let set until firm.

title: campfire stew
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Then add can of soup and a little water.
Heat to simmer for five minutes.

title: dairy bars
directions: Combine sugar, 1/2 cup butter, cocoa and egg and bring to a boil.
Add crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Press in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.
Mix the cream, 1/2 cup butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of crust.
Melt chocolate chips on top.

title: good sugar cookies
directions: Mix as normal.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Flour enough to roll out.
Cut cookies and bake
in moderate oven 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: In large bowl, cream oleo; add sour cream, eggs and muffin mix. Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs in a casserole.
Place crumbs or Fritos on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Remove chicken skin from chicken and debone.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Dredge chicken in cornstarch and cook quickly in hot oil in a large skillet.
Chicken will get opaque.
Add green pepper and onion, stirring for 3 minutes.
Mix chicken stock, salt, sugar, soy sauce and pineapple.
Pour over chicken mixture and heat.
Blend cornstarch with juice and add to skillet, stirring until the sauce is thickened and clear.
(I usually add about 8 whole cherries at this point, for extra color and flavor.) Serve over hot rice.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar and 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Set aside.
Place the other ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until thick. Place 2/3 cup of peanut butter mixture in bottom of pie shell. Spread filling on and sprinkle with rest of peanut butter mixture. Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate-oatmeal no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, butter and milk to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Mix thoroughly. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: white lily angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Set out but do not grease a 10-inch tube pan. Sift flour and 1/4 cup sugar 3 times; set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining cup of sugar. Continue beating until very stiff peaks form.
Sift about 1/4 of the flour mixture over egg whites and gently fold.
Repeat with remaining flour mixture, 1/4 at a time; fold in flavoring.
Spoon batter in tube pan. Run knife through batter to eliminate air pockets.
Bake in lower third of preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Invert pan.
To remove, run knife up and down between cake and pan to loosen it.
Makes 16 servings.
Calories:
126 per slice.
Serve with fresh strawberries and whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: artichokes and green beans romano(4 servings)
directions: In large skillet saute onion and garlic in olive oil until transparent.
Stir in bread crumbs, blending well to absorb oil. Add green beans, artichoke hearts and cheese.
Combine thoroughly yet gently.
Heat slowly to soften cheese. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: twenty-four hour lettuce salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in order given.
Spread mayonnaise, "sealing" to the edge of the bowl.
Cover and chill 24 hours. This will keep several days if refrigerated and not stirred.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed.
Add pineapple, sliced bananas, pecans and sugar.
Chill in refrigerator overnight and then top with Dream Whip.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and parsley in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill about 1 hour until firm enough to work with. Shape into ball (or 2 small balls) and roll in pecans and parsley.

title: anchovy turnovers
directions: Sift flour, measure and sift again into a mixing bowl.
Cut in cream cheese and butter.
Roll into a ball and chill for about 2 hours.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick and cut into 2-inch rounds. Put about 1/4 teaspoon anchovy paste in the center of each round. Moisten edges and press together, turnover fashion.
Prick tops. Place on a baking sheet and chill
until serving time. Then bake in a moderately hot oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Serve at once. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: pumpkin cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Beat with brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Stir in canned pumpkin, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into the unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.
Cool and store in fridge until ready to serve.
Top with whipped cream.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut and beat 4 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Bake in tube cake pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Save broth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour crust on top and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until brown.

title: blue cheese meat balls(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup wine.
Mix well and let stand awhile to marinate.
Shape into bite-size balls.
Brown in small amount of oil.
(Don't overbrown or they will get tough!) Drain cooked meatballs thoroughly on paper towel.
Before serving, place in casserole or chafing dish and add remaining wine.
Heat thoroughly in 350° oven.

title: bacon salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small bite size pieces. Add onion, cheese and bacon.
Mix all with dressing.

title: chocolate pecan pie(makes 2 deep dish pies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Add cocoa and stir until dissolved.
Add hot water and mix well.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add pecans and pour into 2 deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until well set.
(It does not have eggs in it.)

title: stove top mac and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add macaroni.
Stir to coat.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add cranberry juice to sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Put in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and serve.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer spinach, eggs, onions, bacon and peas.
Seal with dressing of sour cream, salad dressing and Ranch dressing.
Top with Swiss cheese and refrigerate.

title: zucchini and cheese casserole
directions: Wash zucchini and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook in small amount of salted water until soft.
Place in casserole.
Combine milk, egg and cheese.
Pour over zucchini. Dot with butter.
Bake in a hot 400° oven until cheese is melted and the top nicely browned.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in the milk; add salt, pepper, onion and eggs.
Add ground beef and pork, olives and celery; mix well. Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Pour mixture of butter, chili sauce and water over top of meat loaf.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake for 1 hour.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in a bag with seasoned flour.
Heat oil in skillet; saute chicken, turning once to brown.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook slowly 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix brown and white sugars together.
Cream butter until soft. Add sugars gradually.
Add egg, peanut butter, salt and soda.
Beat until creamy.
Sift flour before measuring; re-sift and add to batter.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Roll dough into small balls. Place on greased cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 60 medium size cookies.

title: cornflake candy
directions: In pot, bring to a boil over medium heat, corn syrup and sugar.
Take off of stove and add peanut butter and corn flakes. Mix well and drop candy mixture onto waxed paper.
Makes about 40 pieces.

title: country pie
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pat meat into the bottom and pinch, fluting, around the edges of a greased 9-inch pie pan. Bake 10 to 15 minutes before adding the filling.

title: south dakota pie
directions: Mix together and spread on top of layer 1.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli, leaving a little crunchy.
Make a roux with butter and flour.
Add roux to milk, cream and bay leaf and cook until thick.
Using half of the broccoli, whirl cooked mixture in blender after adding herb salt and vegetable cubes.
Chop remainder of the broccoli and add to soup.
Heat to serving temperature.
Sliced, stuffed olives can be used as a garnish. Float them on top with their little red eyes showing.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add this to cream mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork (crisscross).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Cut meat into serving sizes.
Dredge in lightly seasoned flour.
In a skillet, brown meat on both sides.
Place in a crock-pot.
Blend soup and water.
Add to crock-pot.
Cook.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup of dry mix.
Pat remaining mix lightly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice and 1 egg until smooth and light.
Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle with reserved crumb mix.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: crazy dough for kids
directions: Cook all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat 4 to 5 minutes, stirring vigorously until mixture forms a ball. Remove dough from saucepan and let stand on counter for 5 minutes. Knead dough about 30 seconds or until smooth and blended.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Prepare orange Jell-O as directed.
Set aside until cool.
Add remaining ingredients and chill until serving.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let the cake cool completely before turning it out of the pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Set aside. In a larger bowl, beat together margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes until edges are golden.
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Scrape and slice carrots crossways.
Cover with water and boil until tender.
Place chopped onion and pepper in colander.
When carrots are tender, pour boiling water and carrots over bell pepper and onion in colander.
While carrots, pepper and onion are draining, bring to a boil the oil, vinegar and soup.
Stir at low boiling point until oil is well blended into soup.
Mix all ingredients in plastic or glass container; cover and store in refrigerator until well chilled.

title: eggless, butterless and milkless cake
directions: Boil together sugar, water, shortening, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes; cool.
When cold, add soda (dissolved in 1 teaspoon hot water) and flour.
Stir to mix well.
Grease lightly a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 loaf pans; line with wax paper.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: white corn salsa
directions: Place first 5 ingredients along with their juices into a large bowl and stir until the mixture gets to be a consistent melody of colors.
Strain mixture in a colander for 5-10 minutes.
Return mixture to original large bowl and add salt and sugar to taste. Again, stir thoroughly and return mixture to colander to strain for 10 minutes.
Last, return mixture to the bowl again and add 2 tablespoons of olive oil.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate until serving.
Serve with white corn chips or chips of choice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter and place on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until soft peaks form.
Add sugar and whip until stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips gently.

title: mexican rice
directions: In medium size heavy skillet with tight fitting cover, saute onion in hot bacon fat.
Stir in rice, 1 cup green pepper, chili powder, canned tomatoes and salt.
Add 2 cups water; bring to boiling, then reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 20 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed and rice is cooked.
Garnish with chopped tomato and green pepper.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hodgepodge relish
directions: Mix 1/4 cup hot vinegar to 2/3 cup diced cucumber, 1 cup diced tomato, 1/2 cup chopped onion and 1/4 cup chopped celery.
Add 1/2 teaspoon each of celery seed and mustard seed.
Place ingredients in a jar and refrigerate.

title: red cross casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard.
Add bread cubes, sausage and grated cheese to egg mixture.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Add cranberry sauce.
Mash with masher and mix.
Add pineapple and remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and seasonings well; add crabmeat.
Serve with crackers.

title: b.l.t. bites(appetizer)
directions: Cut a thin slice off of each tomato top.
Scoop out and discard pulp.
Invert tomatoes on a paper towel to drain.
In a small bowl, combine all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into tomatoes. Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 16 to 20 appetizer servings.

title: cranberry jello mold
directions: Mix 2 cups boiling water with Jell-O until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and cranberry sauce.
Mix well.
Put in a mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Freeze in Ziploc freezer bags.
To serve, thaw to a mush and add ginger ale to taste.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water well; then add sherbet.
Stir until mixed real well.
Next add Cool Whip and mix well until it is real smooth.
Pour into bowl and chill.

title: lemon whip
directions: Thoroughly chill milk.
Remove from can.
Add sugar; whip with electric mixer.
Add lemon juice, a small amount at a time, while whipping.
Add lemon rind just before mixture will hold shape. Line 2 ice trays (without sections) with waxed paper.
Cover each with 1/4 of the crumbs.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into each tray. Cover with remaining crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: papa rellena
directions: Saute meat, onion and garlic in oil, adding salt, pepper and hot pepper gradually.
Add tomatoes and simmer for at least 10 minutes.
Add raisins, olives, hard-boiled eggs (chopped) and peanuts.

title: picante con queso
directions: Combine Velveeta, milk and picante in saucepan over low heat. Heat, stirring frequently, until sauce is smooth.
Serve with chips.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In skillet, melt butter and saute all chopped ingredients for 5 minutes, then add rest and brown 5 minutes.
Fill caps and bake at 375° for 10 minutes; broil for 4 minutes.
Can do ahead and freeze. Bake first and broil 10 minutes.

title: never soggy pie crust
directions: Blend flour, shortening and salt; add beaten egg mixed with water and vinegar to flour mixture, mixed lightly with fork.
Turn out onto floured board or wax paper.
Bake slowly in 350° oven. Makes 3 pie crusts or 1 double and 1 single crust.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions but without salt.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Beat egg whites with lemon juice until frothy.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff and sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla and pour over pie.

title: brick haus sauerkraut salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add all ingredients remaining.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 or 8 servings.

title: diet chicken and dumplings
directions: Disjoint chicken and remove skin; place in a large pan.
Add water, salt, celery and onion; simmer 1 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove chicken from bone; return chicken to chicken stock.
Bring chicken and stock to a boil; add rolled dumplings. Cover and boil gently 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato special
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into quarters.
Boil in water 3 to 5 minutes; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients (not lemon) together. Place with potatoes in a buttered baking dish.
Drizzle more olive oil over top.

title: shrimp and linguine
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
In large saute pan, melt butter and oil.
Saute shrimp until done.
Add wine and seasoning (oregano, garlic, parsley and basil); simmer a minute.
Heat Marinara sauce. Cook linguine al dente.

title: curried fruit and rice salad
directions: Combine rice, orange, grapes and celery.
Combine mayo, yogurt, curry, lime peel and juice.
Stir dressing into salad. Fold in banana just before serving.

title: coffee cake with peach filling
directions: Mix till crumbly: flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and butter. Take out 1/2 cup for topping. Add eggs and milk to remaining mixture and beat. Spread in buttered 9 x 13 inch pan. Add filling. To remaining crumbs add brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine all soups and chicken broth.
Cube Velveeta cheese and add to sauce.
Stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Add shredded chicken to sauce along with broth from cooked chicken. Stir and pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: mock steak diane
directions: Cut meat into 4 serving size pieces.
Pound to 1/4-inch thickness. Cook meat, two pieces at a time, in hot oil for 2 minutes. Turn and cook 2 minutes more. Remove to warm platter. Cook onion in margarine until just tender.
Add mushrooms, lemon juice, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Heat through.
Spoon over parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: 8 minute cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set at least 4 hours. Garnish with desired topping.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter, chocolate chips.
Put cereal in large bowl.
Pour mixture over cereal and mix until all cereal is covered.
Pour one cup of powdered sugar in a bag and one to 2 cups of cereal mixture and shake.
Do this until sugar and cereal mixture is done.

title: broccoli lasagne
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs; drain and add favorite spaghetti sauce.
Heat undiluted broccoli soup and frozen broccoli.
Cook carrots and onion.
Saute mushrooms; mix together all vegetables.
Beat eggs into Mozzarella and cut up white American cheese.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls thinly over a cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned; let cool.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Bring slowly to a boil and stir constantly for 2 minutes or a little longer, if needed.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until the right thickness to spread smoothly.
I cook mine until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Butter a deep baking pan.
Pour onion soup mix (dry) on bottom of pan, then the uncooked rice.
Place cut up chicken or 4 chicken breasts around rice and soup.
Add the chicken and golden mushroom soups.
Add 1 can of water.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and let set in the refrigerator until well chilled.

title: louise's service casserole
directions: Combine meat, peppers, onion, and asparagus and mix well. Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, margarine, egg, chocolate, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool; frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: poulet luzianne
directions: Place chicken breast halves between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a mallet or rolling pin; set aside.
Saute pecans and next 3 ingredients in butter until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat; add bread cubes, seasonings, apple and apricots, stirring well.
Spoon about 1/3 cup filling onto each chicken breast; fold sides over and secure with wooden picks.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Baste with Apricot Glaze.
Bake uncovered an additional 15 minutes, basting every 5 minutes.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until golden.
Serve with remaining glaze.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown sirloin steak in butter.
Add onion.
Add flour, salt, paprika and mushrooms.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and simmer about 10 minutes.
(This much may be done ahead and reheated later.)
Add sour cream shortly before serving and heat through for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 generous servings. Serve on rice, noodles or Uncle Ben's long grain wild rice.

title: walnut pastries
directions: Mix ingredients.
Make into small ball and chill.

title: broccoli-cheddar egg "bake"(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, beat eggs.
Heat milk on High for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes, until steaming.
Gradually beat into eggs. Stir in bread and remaining ingredients, reserving 2 tablespoons cheese.
With spatula, lightly press bread mixture into egg mixture.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes. Cook casserole, covered, on 50% power for 14 to 17 minutes, until just set.
Tilt casserole dish and, with spatula, gently lift edge of egg mixture twice during cooking to allow the uncooked portion to run toward edge of casserole dish.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: plymouth rock holiday mold
directions: In small bowl, dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in 3/4 cup cold water.
Chill until thickened.
Spoon 1/4 cup gelatin in bottom of 4 cup ring mold.
Arrange apple slices and pecans in gelatin.
Carefully spoon remaining lemon gelatin over fruit and nuts.
In another small bowl, dissolve orange or raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce and lemon juice; chill until thickened, about 3 hours.
Unmold onto serving plate.

title: bananas foster
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Add brown sugar and banana liquor.
Blend in bananas and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Let stand and cool until warm.
Pour over ice cream and serve immediately.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a medium sized baking dish layer the bottom with vanilla wafers and slice the bananas on top of that. In a pot (I use teflon) mix your sugar, cornstarch, and salt
together.

Add 1 c. milk and mix well. Add the eggs and the other c. of milk and mix. Put on medium heat and cook until the mixture begans to thicken and bubble. You will need to stir this almost constantly to prevent it from scorching. When it is thick enough pour over wafers and bananas. Beat the egg whites until
stiff. Add
1/2 c. sugar, 1/2 tsp cream of tarter and 1 tsp. vanilla. Beat again until all is blended and put on top of pudding. Bake in 400 degree oven until topping is golden brown.

title: winter vegetable puree
directions: Peel the vegetables. Chop into medium-size pieces. Cook until soft; drain and mash. You can puree them together or mash and mix together. Add butter (melted), heavy cream, dash of nutmeg, salt and pepper to taste. Mix everything together and mound in a casserole. When ready to serve, microwave 3 to 5 minutes until hot.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Soak chicken in milk for 1 hour.
Mix all dry ingredients and coat chicken.
Spray baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken in dish.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: special k candy
directions: Melt sugar and Karo over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Press into buttered cookie sheet.
Melt butterscotch chips and pour over top of cereal mixture.
Cool; cut and serve.

title: choco chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Fold in chips.
Add flour.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.
After baking, remove quickly to rack.

title: roka cheese ball
directions: Blend thoroughly and roll in a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts (optional).
Place cherry (well drained) on top.
Chill.

title: sue's peanut butter fudge
directions: Prepare a 9 x 13 baking dish by applying a light coating of butter.
Set aside.

title: bean salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine all of the beans, green pepper and onion.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; stir until the sugar dissolves.
Pour over bean mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Bake the shell until brown.
Pour the blueberries in the pie crust.
Set in the refrigerator to cool.

title: red top salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and let melt.
Soften cream cheese and beat. Add mayonnaise and beat until fluffy, add to jello with chopped celery, walnuts and pineapple.
Add whipped cream.
Dissolve cherry jello.
Cool and pour over lime jello and cheese mixture.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Combine ingredients in order listed in large mixing bowl. Blend well.
Transfer to a deep, buttered dish or casserole.
Bake at 300° until firm, about 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream or sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg yolk.
Stir in flour and salt.
Press dough in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, with floured hands.
Beat egg white and water; brush over dough.
Sprinkle with cashew nuts; press lightly.
Bake until light brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Cut into 3-inch squares; cut each square diagonally into halves.
Immediately remove from pan; cool completely.
Drizzle with chocolate.
Let stand until chocolate is set, about 2 hours. Makes 24 triangles.

title: pepper relish
directions: Cover chopped vegetables with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain fully.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and mustard seed. Stir in well.
Slowly bring to boil.
Boil rapidly 10 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: peanut butter sensations
directions: *I use plain Crisco and oleo.

title: salmon patties
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon, discard.
Flake salmon with a fork in a medium size bowl.
Add cracker crumbs, onions, egg and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Let stand 3 to 4 minutes to allow crumbs to soak up some moisture.
Divide into 8 equal potions and roll each portion between palm of hands to form a ball.
Melt butter over low heat in a large frypan.
Add salmon balls leaving space between to allow balls to flatten into patties on cooking. Cook until golden brown turning once.
May serve with cream peas. Makes 4 servings.

title: picante chicken with peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a Reynolds oven cooking bag.
Add picante sauce in bag.
Squeeze bag to blend the ingredients.
Add chicken to bag; turn bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange chicken in an even layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place pepper rings over chicken.
Close bag with tie; cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake until chicken is tender, 35 to 40 minutes.
To serve, stir sauce; spoon over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: succotash
directions: Combine equal amounts of hot cooked corn (from frozen) and hot cooked green lima beans.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika to taste.

title: grandma's rosettes
directions: Beat eggs well; add salt, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour alternately with milk and melted butter.
Let batter rest for 2 hours.

title: lazy-day lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water following package instructions and drain.
Combine oregano, spaghetti sauce and ground beef.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Combine and heat on top of double boiler (hot, not boiling water).
Fill molds; chill in refrigerator.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Peel and dice cucumber, place in strainer and let stand 10 minutes to drain excess liquid.
Mix cucumber with other ingredients and chill well before serving.

title: coffee bracer
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in basket of drip coffeemaker or electric percolator.
Fill pot with water.
Prepare coffee according to manufacturer's instructions.
Stir in brown sugar and extract.
Yields 6 cups (7 calories per 3/4 cup serving).

title: white castle sliders
directions: Mix and pack together in large cookie sheet: ground chuck, onion, soup, pepper, bread crumbs and egg.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Pour off grease.
Cut meat into squares (size of buns).
Sprinkle top of meat with 2 tablespoons of water.
Put meat and buns together and wrap tightly in foil.
Place in Pepperidge Farm container and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
These can be frozen.
Defrost and heat at 300°.

title: tamale pie ole
directions: Combine biscuit mix, cornmeal and water; mix to form a soft dough.
Press on the bottom and sides of a greased 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Stir together chili, chili peppers, corn, olives, sour cream and onion.
Pour over dough and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with grated cheese while hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cut up all vegetables.
Mix all ingredients; chill for 2 hours.

title: tina's spinach and garlic pasta sauce
directions: In saucepan on medium to low heat, melt margarine in oil.
Add minced garlic and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add canned broth and thawed drained spinach.
Simmer.
(Cook 1 pound spaghetti.)
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over pasta.
Add grated cheese to your dish and enjoy!

title: ninth street house tea
directions: Mix tea, sugar, grape juice and lemon juice together in a 1 gallon jug.
Finish filling jug with water.
Makes 1 gallon tea.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Bake cake in square pan. When cake is done, stick holes in it and pour milk over cake.
Pour caramel sauce over cake. Crush one of the Butterfinger candy bars and sprinkle over the cake.
Let cake cool.
Spread Cool Whip over cake. Sprinkle the other Butterfinger over the Cool Whip. Stripe with caramel sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Reserve 1/4 stick butter or margarine and 1/2 cup cracker crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Mix all other ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Gently wash and remove stems from mushrooms.
Saute caps in butter.
Drain on paper towel.
Add finely chopped stems to skillet.
Saute with shallots that have been chopped.
Squeeze lemon juice on stems and caps.
Add crabmeat to skillet along with seasonings.
Add crumbs and mix well.
Over low heat, add beaten egg while stirring constantly.
Stuff mixture into mushroom caps. (If too small, shape into mounds to have more stuffing.)
Bake on a cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes in a 325° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix well the first 5 ingredients.
Add the shortening, butter and bananas; beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add the buttermilk and unbeaten eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Pour into prepared pans (2).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: super chicken nachos
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces; fry until done.
Warm refried beans in microwave for about 2 minutes.
Slice onions and olives. Put tortilla chips on cookie sheet.
Top with refried beans, olives, onions, salsa and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Garnish with sour cream.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, garlic powder, ginger and honey. Stir together.
Put ingredients in a Ziploc bag along with the steak.
Marinate 4 hours or overnight.
Place steak on broiler or barbecue grill.
Baste often with remaining marinade sauce.
You can reserve remaining marinade sauce for another meal.
Serves 4.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water about 2 or 3 minutes. Drain.
Saute meat, onions, garlic and seasoning until onions are transparent.
Stir in rice and tomato sauce.
Blend cottage cheese and egg.
Arrange half of zucchini slices in a buttered shallow pan (2-quart casserole).
Spoon mixture over zucchini, then arrange rest of zucchini on top.
Place in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy skillet potatoes
directions: In large skillet, cook celery, onion and garlic in hot butter until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add broth, water, potatoes, carrots and pepper to skillet.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Uncover; over medium heat, simmer 5 minutes or until broth is slightly thickened, stirring often.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: instant cheese cake
directions: Blend in blender for 45 seconds the hot water, unflavored gelatin and lemon juice.
Add and blend for 10 seconds the egg yolks, cream cheese and sugar.
Add and blend for 10 seconds the whipping cream and vanilla, then add one at a time and blend after each 15 to 20 ice cubes.
Pour into crust.
I like graham cracker crust.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Saute mushrooms in oil for 5 minutes.
Remove them from heat and add butter flavoring (you can substitute real butter or margarine, just add about 1/2 tablespoon) and pepper and set aside.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in 1 cup hot water in a separate pan.
Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water.
Stir into bouillon and simmer until thickened.
Add mushrooms and wine, simmering for 2 to 3 minutes.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of gravy.

title: cereal snack meringues
directions: Heat oven
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites in
a
large
bowl
until foamy.
Gradually beat in sugar and
continue beating until very stiff and glossy.	Fold in cereal and
chocolate
chips.
Drop
mixture by teaspoon 2 inches apart on	cookie sheet.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: lefse
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cooled potatoes, cream and butter.
Mix well. Add salt and flour (just enough to make dough easy to handle).
Roll out thin on floured board.
Bake on a 500° lefse griddle.
Turn and bake on the other side.
Makes 30 lefse.

title: fried pig feet
directions: When pig feet become cold, split and fry in hot butter or dip in batter and fry in hot fat for 15 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix all together; put in Pam sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut in small squares.
Can be reheated.

title: praline cheesecake(must prepare ahead.  serves 16.)
directions: In a large bowl, combine crumbs, sugar and melted butter. Press into the bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake crust in 350° oven for 10 minutes; let cool in pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; mix in sauce and mushrooms.
Put 1/2 in a 2-quart dish.
Spread cheese; add remaining hamburger mix.
Add cheese on top.
Pour 2/3 cup milk on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamed tortillas
directions: Heat cream cheese, beef, olives and peppers in microwave until soft.
Mix well.
Spread cream cheese on tortilla shell and roll. Cut into pieces and chill.

title: steak sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in a sauce pan. Place pan over
low heat and stir until butter is blended with condiments. Be careful not to let it curdle. Pour over steak before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add bananas; blend.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix only until blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter; add other ingredients and mix.
Form in shape of crescent.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven until slightly brown.
Remove from oven and roll in powdered sugar.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Pour dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add all other ingredients and chill for 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: gone all day stew
directions: Mix together soup, water, flour until smooth, combine with remaining ingredients in roasting pan.
Cover and bake at 275 for 4 to 5 hours.
(I added another cup water late in baking.)

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough to oblong shape.
Spread a thin layer of mustard and spices.
Place on pepperoni, sausage and veggies, if desired. Roll up and pinch ends.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one-week slaw
directions: Combine shredded cabbage, carrot and chopped onion.
Pour sugar over these. Bring to a boil the vinegar, salt, mustard and celery seed.
Add oil and bring to a boil again.
Pour hot vinegar and oil mixture over the slaw mixture. Cover tightly and chill. Don't stir until you are ready to serve the slaw.
Keeps well for up to 1 week!

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef in bacon grease or oil in an iron skillet or large frying pan; drain.
Season with salt and brown sauce or barbecue sauce.
To this, add onion, green pepper, tomatoes, rice, celery, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Leave these ingredients spread over meat in layers as they are.
Cover and cook very slowly on low heat for 1 hour.
Serve with a large spoon without stirring.
Makes a wonderful meal served with salad and rolls.

title: zippy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well; bring to boil.
Simmer 25 minutes.

title: fettuccine primavera
directions: Blanch the broccoli and cauliflower in boiling water.
Rinse in cold water to stop cooking process; drain and set aside.
Heat the butter in a saucepan; saute the onion, carrot and mushrooms until tender.
Add the flour and stir.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add the cream, broccoli and cauliflower.
Reduce to simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the pimento, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Cook noodles al dente in boiling, salted water.
Drain.
Place noodles in a large serving bowl.
Pour sauce over and serve.
Garnish with black olives.
Serves 8.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Using an 11 x 7-inch pan, mix the first 5 ingredients and put into the greased pan.
Top with bacon and olives and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This recipe may be made ahead of time and cooked when ready to use.

title: spoon biscuits
directions: Add milk, a little at a time, to flour.
Mix to a batter with a tablespoon.
When thick, spoon in pan.
Use your finger to put in pan.
Will make 6 or 8 biscuits.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Blend all ingredients together and re-freeze.
For 1 serving, mix 2 tablespoons mix, 1 cup hot water and 1 jigger rum.

title: amaretto bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Lightly brown almonds in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Sprinkle over bottom of prepared pan.
Set aside.
Mix cake mix, eggs, Amaretto, water and vegetable oil. Beat well for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over nuts.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Mix sugar, 1/2 cup margarine, Amaretto and water in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over hot cake while still in pan.
Remove from pan after 1 hour.

title: caramel sauce(2 quarts)
directions: Mix sugars and flour.
Stir into water.
Boil gently until thickened.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream or apple desserts.

title: matt's favorite pie
directions: In a bowl, mix together eggs and milk.
Gradually add in lime peel and lime juice.
Stir in whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust and freeze 3 hours.
Serve with a spoonful of whipped topping on top.

title: fish chowder
directions: Simmer haddock in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes; drain. Reserve broth.
Remove bones from fish.
Saute diced salt pork until crisp.
Remove pork; reserve fat and saute onions until brown.
Add fish, potatoes, celery, bay leaf, salt and pepper. Pour in fish broth which was reserved and enough water to make 3 cups of liquid.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: lemon-lime refrigerator sheet cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 3/4 c. boiling water, add 1/2 cup cold water; set aside at room temperature.
Mix and bake cake as directed in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cool cake 20 - 25 minutes.
Poke deep holes through top of warm wake while still in pan about 1 inch apart.
Slowly pour gelatin mixture into holes.
Refrigerate.

title: haystacks
directions: Boil to a soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add shredded coconut.
Shape into cones and cool.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine gelatin, sugar and 3/4 cup of water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve gelatin and sugar, then remove from heat and add fruit.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and condensed milk in bowl until smooth.
Combine with gelatin mixture and pecans, mixing well.
Pour into a 2-quart mold or dish.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on serving dish.
Serves 16.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples or drain canned apples in a bowl. Combine apples, applesauce, flour, Sweet 'N Low, salt and spices. Mix well.
Pour in pie pan lined with one pie crust and seal edges. Slice vents in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Mix corn meal, salt and soda.
Add eggs (beaten), milk, corn, bacon drippings, onion and peppers.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into large 2-inch deep casserole dish, greased.
Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 15 to 20 minutes.

title: amazin' raisin cake
directions: Beat first 10 ingredients in large bowl for 2 minutes, scraping bowl frequently or beat by hand vigorously 300 times. Batter will be very thick.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove and cool.

title: winter watermelon cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O, sour cream, water, oil and eggs. Blend, then beat for 4 minutes.
Stir in crumbled cookies.
Pour into a greased and floured fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookie
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter.
Pour this mixture over the cereal and coconut; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream together oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together baking powder, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix in vanilla, zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: fancy peanut soup(serves 12)
directions: In a pan over low heat, soften the peanut butter to allow for easy mixing with the milk.
Add the milk, salt, pepper and vegetable seasoning mixture.
Bring to a boil and then set aside. Saute the onion and celery in butter; do not allow to brown.
Stir in the flour as if making a gravy.
Add the chicken stock and stir constantly until the mixture comes to a boil.
It save a lot of time and elbow grease if the stock has already been brought to a boil.
Remove from the heat.
Combine with the peanut butter and milk mixture.
Return to the stove and over a very low heat, cook until all the ingredients are well blended.

title: pink cloud cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions. Bake in two 9 x 1 1/2-inch layer cake pans. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in 1/2 cup cold water. Set aside for 20 minutes. Cool cake 5 minutes in pans. Remove. Place on racks over waxed paper. Using long-tined fork, punch holes in cake, making even rows across cake surface. Spoon gelatin over cake. Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar in a bowl until light.
Add cooled melted butter, milk and vanilla or Ovaltine.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gently fold into batter.
Bake and serve.
Makes 10 (4 1/2-inch square) waffles.

title: hubcaps lesh's lemon chess pie
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs, cornmeal, butter, sugar, lemon juice and grated rind, milk and salt.
Pour the mixture into the pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 25 minutes or until the filling is just set and the crust and filling are browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare the pudding with the directions on the box, then mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: apple bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix 1 cup sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Mix 1 teaspoon sugar and the cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan; cool bread completely before slicing.
Store tightly covered.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Lightly
brown
chopped
onion
in
shortening.
Pour in cream of celery soup and other ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 1 quart
casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften; combine with Cheddar cheese and Lipton onion soup.
Roll in logs or balls; roll in pecans or dried parsley flakes.

title: rice custard pudding
directions: Heat water to boiling. Remove from heat. Stir in rice. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt; slowly stir in milk. Stir in rice. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Place casserole in baking pan. Pour in very hot water (1 1/4-inch deep) for water bath. Bake 70 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Serve warm or cool.

title: mama's mayo cake
directions: Sift together the flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Cream together the sugar and mayonnaise.
Add sifted ingredients to creamed mixture, alternately with cold water, beating after each addition. Add the vanilla. Bake at 350° until done.
This cake is soft and moist!

title: avocado salad
directions: Peel avocado, remove seed and chop meat very fine.
Toss with remaining ingredients in a salad bowl until thoroughly combined, with oil and seasoning.
Serves 6.

title: pear pie
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour pears; sweeten to taste with apple pie spice sprinkled on pears.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pears; use a fork to stick all through for juice to come on cake mix.
Spread pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cube bread and put half in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole. Cube cream cheese and place on top of bread.
Cover cheese with rest of bread.
Beat eggs, maple syrup, milk, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour over bread and cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese with Bisquick to coat.
Stir in milk until soft dough forms.
Drop on cookie sheet or roll and cut out.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: peanut butter and carrot cookies
directions: In a
small
bowl
mix
flour and soda together and set aside. In
large
bowl
beat oleo for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars and beat until fluffy, then add carrots, egg whites
and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Stir in oats. Drop
by teaspoonful
on
ungreased cookie sheet and bake for about 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: holiday wreath
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in food coloring.
Add corn flakes cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Using 1/4 cup dry measure coated with cooking spray, evenly portion warm cereal mixture.
Using buttered fingers, quickly shape into individual wreaths or 1 large one.
Dot with cinnamon candies.

title: purple lady salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and undrained blueberries.
Fold in whipping cream or Cool Whip, banana and nuts.
Pour in pan and chill.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: By adding chopped pickles, chives, pimentos, Blue cheese or melted American cheese,
a dressing can be varied to ever so many different ones to fit the special salad according to the vegetables in it.

title: cheaters lasagna
directions: Cook the beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, tomato paste, water, salt and oregano in frying pan until brown.
Whip together the Miracle Whip, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Use an 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 2-quart dish.
Put cooked noodles in greased dish.
Put half of cheese mixture on top of noodles.
Put beef on next and the rest of cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: company breakfast bake
directions: Brown the sausage and drain excess fat.
Mix other ingredients and add to the cooled sausage.
Place in buttered 9 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place in refrigerator covered overnight or several hours.
Next morning, bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350° or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
If you prefer, you can substitute bacon that has been fried and crumbled or ham in place of the sausage.
This is very good and a nice dish to fix when you have company overnight.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: Cook cauliflower about 6 minutes in boiling, salted water until just tender.
Drain.
Combine with celery.
Put into 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole.

title: cabbage bake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and melted margarine together and set aside.
Cook and drain cabbage.
Mix cheese and soup with cooked cabbage.
Layer crackers and cabbage in a 2-quart baking dish, beginning and ending with cracker crumbs.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Mix pudding and put in refrigerator. Cool cake.
Spread pineapple on cake.
Mix pudding when it gets cold with cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Beat.
Spread on cake and sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Stick on cherries.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine (cut up in small pieces) and coconut.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan and bake in oven until brown.
Remove and place apples on crust in pan.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar and pour on top of apples.
Mix egg yolks and sour cream and pour on top of cake.
Bake in oven at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: parmesan oven fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing and dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, bone-side down, in a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: impossible coconut custard pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender on high speed. Count to 10 slowly. Pour into well-greased glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well together and pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate nut crunch
directions: Line lightly greased pan with vanilla wafers and nuts.
Cream together the powdered sugar and shortening.
Add the well beaten egg yolks, chocolate and vanilla.
Add the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Spread mixture over crumbs with knife.
Sprinkle layer of crumbs and nuts on top.
Chill.
Serve with Cool Whip and cherries on top.
Serves 20.

title: magic muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Stir until moistened. Pour batter into greased or paper lined muffin pan. Fill cups 3/4 full. Bake 10 to 20 minutes or until center is firm to the touch. Makes 12 muffins.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with peel still on them until medium soft; let cool.
Fry bacon until crispy, crumble.
Cut up celery and onions. Boil eggs.
Peel the peel off of potatoes, smash up with hands. Add bacon, onions and celery.
Add salad dressing and vinegar. Peel shell off of eggs, smash with hands.
Mix and stir with hands. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate covered apples
directions: Using a double boiler heat water to melt 3 bags of chocolate. Add flavoring if you like.
Take the stick and inset it into apple.
Dip apple all the way in, remove and set on wax paper.
I usually dip 1/2 chocolate and 1/2 white chocolate, but be creative.
When apple dries dip in white chocolate 1/2 way.
Let cool on wax paper.
Melt caramel over double boiler.
Use a lollipop stick and drizzle the caramel over the dipped apple, making a pretty design.
Let cool on wax paper.
Finish by taking gold, red or green ribbon and making a bow on base of stick close to apple.
Set in the decorative box that has green grass in it and give as a gift.

title: carbonara
directions: Cut up bacon into little pieces.
Fry on medium.
Boil pasta while cooking bacon.
Also beat eggs with spices while bacon is frying and pasta is boiling.
Suggested spices are praise allah, garlic salt, black pepper, white pepper, red pepper, onion powder, parsley and Greek seasoning.
Take bacon out and add cooking wine to bacon grease and simmer.
Drain pasta and let cool slightly (2 minutes).
Add egg mixture to pasta.
When alcohol smell is gone from wine and grease sauce, pour over pasta and put the bacon in. Mix.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: wedding chicken
directions: Mix liquid ingredients.
Add chicken.
Melt 1 stick oleo in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour off oleo and add mixture.
Cover with crushed Ritz cracker crumbs.
Pour melted oleo on top of cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with poppy seed (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Great frozen; only add topping when ready to cook.
Thaw before baking.

title: strawberry candies
directions: Combine milk, coconut, 1 package gelatin, almonds, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Shape mixture into strawberries.
Roll candies in remaining gelatin, coating thoroughly.
Let dry until firm. Make leaves with icing on top of candies.
Store in covered container.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: cheese soup
directions: Dice vegetables very small.
Place all ingredients, except ham, in 5-quart saucepan.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add Cheese Sauce (recipe follows) and heat.
Do not boil.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking dish, melt the butter. Sprinkle the graham crackers on top of butter.
Then sprinkle the coconut.
Then sprinkle the chocolate chips.
Then sprinkle the butterscotch chips.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all this. Sprinkle the nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bars.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Mix jello, gelatine, hot water and cold water; stir well.
Mix cranberry sauce and lemon juice.
Chill until thick.
Mix crushed pineapple, oranges and chopped nuts.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.

title: garlic bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small saucepan over medium heat, melt butter and mix with garlic powder and dried parsley.
Place Italian bread on a medium baking sheet.
Using a basting brush, brush generously with butter mixture.
Bake in the preheated oven approximately 10 minutes, until lightly toasted.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle with mozzarella cheese and any remaining butter mixture. Return to oven approximately 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted and bread is lightly browned.

title: lemon snowballs
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and lemon.
Add and beat eggs until smooth.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Add alternately with lemon juice and water.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: foolproof cheese souffle
directions: Spread 8 slices
of
white bread with butter.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Grate
1 pound sharp cheese. Grease casserole and put in alternate layers of cheese and bread.
Beat 6 eggs. Mix well with 3/4
teaspoon
salt, 3 cups milk and dash of red pepper. Add Worcestershire sauce for flavor.
Pour over cheese and
bread. Let
stand
in refrigerator, covered, for several hours
or overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, uncovered. If half recipe is used, reduce baking time to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Chill overnight. Shape into 2 balls or 2 logs. Roll in pecans and parsley. Serve with veggies and crackers.

title: walnut walkaways
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Combine flour and salt in mixing bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add yeast and egg.
Mix just until blended.
Roll dough 1/2 at a time on a floured surface to a 13x9 rectangle.
Beat cream cheese add sugar and peels until light and fluffy.
Spread half of mixture in each rectangle piece of dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Roll up starting with the 13 inch side.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden.

title: brunch egg souffle
directions: Beat egg, milk, salt and mustard.
Add cheese, bread and sausage.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch or 8 x 11-inch pan and cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cut in squares for serving.
Can double or triple for larger groups.
Hold well in warm oven.

title: breakfast fried rice(serves 4)
directions: Fry corned beef in a large frying pan over medium heat, stirring occasionally until all fat nodules disappear.
Then remove from pan.
Saute garlic and green onions in the corned beef liquid until all onion is glossy, then remove and add to corned beef.
Add butter/oil to the pan, then scramble the eggs in the butter/oil. Then, when cooked to your taste, remove from the pan.

title: creamsicle pie
directions: Beat orange juice.
Blend in ice cream.
Fold in whipped topping until smooth.
Pour in crust.
Freeze immediately at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.
In summer, work fast to avoid melting.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Bring rhubarb, water and sugar to boil. Add Jell-O.
Mix well and set aside.
Grease 9 x 13 cake pan and put miniature marshmallows all over bottom.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine,
mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed. Spread on top inside of rolls.
On bottom half of rolls layer with cheese, then
ham and then cheese again.
Put rolls back together and on top of roll spread on some of the remaining butter mixture. Cover
with
foil
and bake at 275° until cheese melts.
Serves 20 rolls.

title: see's fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk 10 minutes.
After mixture comes to a boil, mix chips, marshmallow cream, vanilla, nuts and butter in a large bowl.
Pour cooked mixture over dry ingredients and stir (not beat) until creamy.
Remember, do not beat!
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: mexican turkey stuffing
directions: Slightly beat egg, then add other ingredients.
Stuff cavity of bird.
Bake at 375° for 3 hours.
After 3 hours, get the hell out of the kitchen because that popcorn is going to blow that turkey's ass right out of the oven!

title: taco salad
directions: Add soup, taco mix, garlic and shredded cheese to cooked, drained hamburger.
Stir until melted.
Cool and add sour cream.

title: herb chicken
directions: Grease dish (7 x 11-inch).
Sprinkle rice in bottom.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken and undiluted cream of chicken soup.
Pour milk over top.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake, covered, with foil at 325° for 1 hour. Bake, uncovered, for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix everything except vanilla and soda in a glass bowl.
Cook 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 4 more minutes.
Stir.
Cook 2 minutes. Add vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Sprinkle soda over mixture.
Stir quickly.
Pour into greased cookie sheet. When cold, turn over and break with spoon.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Add vanilla and egg whites and blend in well.
Bake in 3 round greased and floured cake pans at 350° until golden brown.
Cool and frost with coconut cake frosting.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl; add milk.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocoberry refresher
directions: In blender, place yogurt, milk, chocolate syrup and strawberry syrup.
Cover; blend until smooth.
Makes 8 one cup servings.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to the flour mixture, stirring just until well blended.
Pour batter onto grids of waffle baker that have been slightly greased.
Close lid quickly; do not open during baking.
Use fork to remove baked waffles.
Top with fresh fruit or yogurt.
Makes 12 (4-inch) square waffles. Serves 6.

title: pumpkin freeze
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with gingersnaps (sides, too!).
Melt the ice cream; mix with pumpkin and cinnamon.
Mix, pour into pan and freeze.

title: "sandra's" after dinner drink
directions: Serve liqueur in chocolate cup.
Drink liqueur and eat chocolate.

title: apple tea bread
directions: Cream butter and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine applesauce and sorghum.
Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce mixture to egg mixture; fold in raisins and nuts.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan starting with onion, celery, red pepper, peas, Swiss cheese and lettuce, broken into pieces, eggs and bacon.
Spread Miracle Whip on top and sprinkle sugar on Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over sugar.
Do not mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serve as is.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat yolks until smooth.
Add Eagle Brand milk gradually.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Serve cold.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Steam broccoli until partially cooked, approximately 5 minutes. Transfer to processor or blender and chop fine.
Beat eggs well in a large bowl.
Add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix thoroughly.
Stir in cheese, broccoli and onion.
Spoon into prepared dish, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt. Bake until set, 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut into bite size pieces.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; drain grease.
In casserole dish, layer pork chops, potatoes, onion and soup.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix pudding mix with sugar; add condensed milk, vanilla and chocolate syrup.
Mix well and add milk to thin.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer container and add enough milk to fill 3/4 full. Let ripen one hour before serving.

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix nectar, dates and apricots in saucepan; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add orange rind.
Set aside.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together; blend in shortening and sugar.
Add this to the hot mixture.
Add egg, cream and nutmeats.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 bread pans that are well greased, until 2/3rds full.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Slide out of tins immediately after baking and cool.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil and garlic.
When garlic turns brown, remove.
Add beef; fry a few minutes.
Season with black pepper. Add bouillon; continue to cook a few seconds.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Add.
Cook, stirring until sauce thickens. Add peppers, mushrooms, water chestnuts and ginger.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over steamed rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into two (9-inch) pie crusts. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Combine all ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° about 1 hour. Let stand before serving, as it will thicken up some.
The rice absorbs the liquid.
(I put water chestnuts in mine and I put the parsley and pepper on the top.
I have already added a little more rice and then a little more juice to make a little more.)

title: pecan squares
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar.
Beat with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare Chocolate Crumb Crust; set aside.

title: quiche
directions: Fold in heated cream, eggs, onion, cheese, bacon, mushrooms and green pepper.
Mix together with dash of salt and pepper. Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a casserole dish.
Combine ingredients in order given in a mixing bowl, except crushed potato chips.
Spoon mixture into a buttered dish and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake for 30 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: cavatini
directions: Using about 1/2 box of each variety of noodles, combine all 3 and cook until desired consistency.
Combine the pasta, spaghetti sauce, onions and peppers in a glass casserole dish.
Place sliced pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and cook for an additional 10 minutes.
Best when served with garlic bread and a chef salad.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and water. Add salt, oil and flour.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix well. Sift in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add beer, mixing well. Fold in nuts.
Bake in tube pan, lightly greased, for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken lynn
directions: Put chicken in dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with crackers and a little butter.
Cook 30 minutes until bubbly hot.
Can be served with rice or noodles.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces; combine sugar, cornstarch and apple cider in a saucepan. Cook until thickened. Cool and mix with fruits. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: savory patties
directions: Wash soybeans and soak in 3 cups water overnight.
Save 1 1/4 cups of this water and drain the rest.
Grind soybeans with saved water.
Mix soybeans with oatmeal; let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in other ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls into oiled skillet.
Cover and cook on moderate heat until browned on both sides.
Serve with sauce, tomato, mushroom or whatever desired.

title: stuffed pasta shells
