directions: Saute onion and ground beef until crumbly.
Add spices; cool mixture in
a bowl.
Cook shells according to package directions. Mix Ricotta into ground beef mixture.
Fill shells with ground beef mix and place in 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Crush garlic in small bowl; mix with oil and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Bake bread cubes until brown and set aside.
Cook eggs one minute in boiling water, then cool.
Mix lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in large bowl.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Drain remaining oil from garlic; pour over lettuce.
Break eggs over salad and toss well.
Pour on lemon mixture, bread cubes and cheese.
Toss well and serve at once.

title: special "k" and peanut butter candy
directions: Peel tater 'n thru a sieve, slowly add sugah while tater is still hot.
Keep this heah up till you've gat a stiff dough.
Roll this betwixt two sheets uv wax paper to about a 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread wid a layer uv peanut butter 'n roll up lak you duz a jelly roll.
Chill and slice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with butter.
Place in bottom of sheet cake pan.
Mix sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla flavoring. Spread over crust.
Slice bananas.
Spread drained crushed pineapple over bananas.
Sprinkle with pecans. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with cherries.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Italian dressing package and sour cream.
Pour dressing over vegetables and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: egg foo yung
directions: Coarsely chop chicken, shrimp and mushrooms. Mince green onions and celery. Beat eggs. Blend in salt. Stir in chicken, shrimp, mushrooms, onions, celery and bean sprouts. Heat 1/2 tablespoon oil in an 8-inch frypan over medium-high heat. Reduce heat to medium. Pour 1/4 cup egg mixture into frypan. Cook 1 minute on each side (should be lightly browned). Keep warm in a 200° oven. Repeat until all batter is used, adding more oil as needed. Serve with Foo Yung Sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Put oats in large mixing bowl and set aside.
In sauce pan combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Let come to boil on medium heat.
Take off heat and add vanilla.
Add mixture to oats and stir.
Spoon onto waxed paper and chill.

title: oyster dressing for turkey
directions: Combine margarine and oil in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Soak bread in cold water and squeeze dry.
Add bread, parsley, seasonings, oysters and eggs to sauteed mixture. Cook, stirring, over low heat until bread is lightly browned.

title: low sugar fudge walnut pie
directions: In a medium bowl, stir melted chocolate into sour cream.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in walnuts.
Pour into pie shell; top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chocolate curls and walnuts.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside. In a saucepan, place the water, margarine, oil and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients, mixing well.
Mix together the buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate mixture the butter mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: candy date roll
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms a soft ball when put in cold water.
Add vanilla, then dates.
Cook until it recedes from sides of pan.
Cool.
Add butter and beat until creamy; add nuts and coconut.
Form into rolls.
Place on oiled paper and set in refrigerator.
Slice when cold.

title: orange fluff
directions: Sprinkle jello over Cool Whip and blend.
Add cottage cheese. Fold in drained crushed pineapple and chill.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: shrimp and cheese ball
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients, then blend in shrimp, salt and pepper.
Form into ball.
Chill.
Roll in chopped walnuts. Refrigerate or freeze.
Serve with crackers.

title: nannie crocker's corn pudding
directions: Preheat your oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for approximately 45 to 60 minutes until golden brown.

title: zesty microwave baked beans
directions: Place bacon in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with paper towel; cook on High for 4 minutes.
Remove towel and bacon; reserve drippings in casserole dish.
Crumble bacon; set aside. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered with paper towel, on High for 10 minutes, stirring twice.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Mix well with other ingredients and put in greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 1 hour, covered, at 375°.
Can use leftover turkey (2 to 3 cups).

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Mix everything else and pour over potatoes.
Bake a little over an hour at 350°.

title: rice dressing
directions: Cut or chop pepper, celery and onion into very small bite size pieces.
Season to taste and pour all ingredients into a skillet or pan.
Steam for 10 minutes or until pepper, onion and celery are tender.
Cook turkey necks or gizzards normally.
Season and cook until very tender.
Set aside for cooling.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onions in fat.
Add tomato soup, beans, salt and pepper.
Mix chili powder, sugar, vinegar and water. Stir into the meat.
Mix uncooked macaroni in last.
Cook in covered dish at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground
beef,
onions
and jalapeno together.
Mix meal, soda, salt,
milk, eggs and corn together, put a layer of meal mixture, then a layer of grated cheese, then meat mixture. Bake in iron skillet for 30 to 40 minutes in 400° oven.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix with cut apples.
Put into pie shell.
Add butter in slices.
Cover with top crust.
Cook at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: macaroni salad(small shell macaroni)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Garnish with Spanish and black olives and egg slices, if desired.

title: bonbons
directions: Mix all together and roll into balls.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with 3 cups milk; chill until thick.
Add sour cream and nuts; mix well.
In large container, put a layer of crumbled cake, next a layer of pudding mix, then a layer of cherry pie filling.
Repeat this method again.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: holly cookies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in pan over low heat.
Add food coloring, then corn flakes.
Spoon out onto wax paper; top with 2 cinnamon candies.

title: delicious shrimp appetizer
directions: Mix together catsup and horseradish to make an ample amount to horseradish sauce.
Drain shrimp and add to sauce.
Spread cream cheese over crackers and then spread shrimp mix onto cream cheese and crackers.
Serve on a platter.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Cut up the chicken into serving size pieces.
Combine the soups and wine and pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli, cauliflower, carrot bake
directions: Cook broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.
Drain.
Put into casserole dish.
Mix together mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, instant rice and Cheddar cheese.

title: best banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Then add remaining ingredients. Bake in grease, large loaf pan at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Stir together the first 4 ingredients.
Add shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water and add with buttermilk.
Stir together with flour mixture.
Mix well and turn out on floured board.
If needed, add more flour to make soft dough.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Brush with melted butter.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with Triscuits.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: cinnamon apple rolls
directions: Combine the raisins and apple juice in a small bowl.
Allow to sit for at least 1 hour. You might want to soak the raisins overnight in the refrigerator.
Grease two 9 inch cake pans. After the dough has risen the first time and has been punched down, divide the dough in half. Roll each portion to a rectangle 9x12 inches.
Brush each rectangle with melted butter. In a small bowl, combine the sugar, cinnamon, and pecans. Stir to mix. Sprinkle this mixture over the buttered dough.
Drain the raisins and sprinkle over the sugar mixture.
Roll the dough jelly-roll fashion, starting with the 12 inch side. Cut into slices 3/4 to 1 inch thick.
Place the slices cut side down in the cake pans. Cover and allow to rise in a warm place for about 45 minutes or until doubled.
Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Pour 1/3 cup of the cream over each pan of rolls.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove from the oven and turn the rolls out onto a plate.
Invert onto another plate so that rolls will be upright. Cool slightly.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in heat-proof bowl.
Pour evaporated milk in
a 2 cup glass measuring cup and add enough water to measure 2 cups.
Whisk eggs and 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix into sugar mixture.
Stir.
Add rest of milk.
Place bowl over simmering water and cook, stirring constantly, 12 to 15 minutes until thick. Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts.
Place plastic over.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Stir; pour into shell.
Cover.
Refrigerate 3 hours until set.

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard for liquid.
Layer the bread, cheese, broccoli, ham, onion, more bread (cut with donut cutter).
Put all this in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Pour liquid over this. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter surprises
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream first six ingredients together until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually stir dye ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir in chopped butter cups.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheet and cool on wire racks.
Yield:
approx. 5 dozen cookies.

title: steak surprise
directions: Brown steaks in oil on both sides.
Drain thoroughly and place in baking dish.
Mix together all of the other ingredients in a large bowl and pour over steaks.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving the juice.
Set pineapple aside. In a saucepan, combine juice with sugar, eggs and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium-low heat until slightly thickened.
Remove from the heat; cool.
Stir in pineapple, celery, apples and pecans.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for about 15 minutes before cutting.
Serve on lettuce-lined plates, if desired.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and bake on a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with English peas and carrots.

title: lemon mint zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini in water, broth, mint, savory and soy sauce about 4 minutes.
Put solids with a little liquid into processor. Puree then strain into saucepan.
Add wine, lemon juice and rest of cooking liquid.
Taste; add bouillon cubes if needed.
If too thin, thicken with 1 to 3 tablespoons cornstarch, moistened with 1 to 3 tablespoons water.
Serves 4.
Serve warm or cold with a dollop of sour cream or yogurt.

title: brownies
directions: Mix oleo and brown sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Sift and mix in the salt, flour and baking powder.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut while hot.
Makes 35.

title: acini de pepe fruit salad
directions: Cook and drain acini de pepe (macaroni).
Drain crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Save juice.

title: old-fashioned blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In medium bowl, combine cornstarch, sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.

title: lemon pie
directions: Juice lemons.
Mix Eagle Brand, eggs and lemon juice. Stir well.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in pie shells and chill.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the oleo, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Add soda and vanilla; stir well.
Pour over popped corn in large pan.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; heat, stirring occasionally, over low heat until it is thick enough to serve.
You can double the recipe if you want to serve more.

title: ginger ale salad
directions: Mix seasoning into ginger ale.
Add melted gelatin.
Pour into mold.
When begins to thicken, add fruit.
Serve with mayonnaise.

title: pistachio mallow salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine whipped topping and pudding mix. Fold in the marshmallows and pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Yield: 12 servings.

title: vegetable rice medley
directions: In a saucepan, combine the rice, water, soup mix, and salt; bring to a boil.
Add the vegetables; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook until rice and vegetables are tender.

title: incredible carrot cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, mayonnaise, and pineapple. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with cream cheese icing.

title: orange blossom mini muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients in cake mix.
Coat mini muffin tins with nonstick cooking spray.
Fill cups about 2/3 full and bake in a 350° preheated oven for 15 minutes.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in salted water until "al dente".
Rinse and drain. Cook asparagus 5 to 7 minutes; refresh in ice water.
Combine Italian dressing, vinegar and seasonings; mix with vegetables and pasta.
Refrigerate until needed.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry "krispie" dessert
directions: Soften vanilla ice cream.
Melt butter.
Add and dissolve brown sugar.
Add coconut and cereal.
Spread and pat half of mixture into bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Evenly distribute 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream into pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Serve with thawed strawberries or fresh strawberries sweetened with sugar.

title: a dark secret
directions: Mix together, spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in slow oven 325° for 45 minutes.
When cooled cut into squares and roll in powdered sugar.

title: orange fluff
directions: Combine pineapple and gelatin in a saucepan.
Heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Cool.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in Cool Whip.
Put in a mold or dish.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Place 2 packages unflavored gelatin in a bowl.	Add 1/4 cup cold water;
stir.	Add
cup boiling water to mixture after dissolved.	Add
condensed	milk,
then
1	cup
boiling water.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Roll out crescent rolls on cookie sheet and bake.
Mix together mayonnaise, Hidden Valley and cream cheese.
Spread on cool crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables.
Cut in squares.

title: tracy's strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Add 1/2 cup of pecans to mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
When done, mix Jell-O according to box.
Punch holes in cake and pour Jell-O over cake.
Put this in refrigerator to cool.
When cool, put first layer on cake box and ice it, then put the drained, frozen strawberries on first layer.
Apply second layer.
Ice entire cake. Garnish with fresh strawberries and remaining pecans.

title: a-p cakes
directions: Mix and pour into round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients except pepper and barbecue sauce.
Cover both sides of meat and let stand overnight in refrigerator, covered with foil.
Add pepper. Cover with foil and cook 5 hours at 300°.
The last hour, uncover and add barbecue sauce.

title: cookie surprise
directions: Put milk in small bowl.
Dip chocolate chip cookies in milk and make one layer in pan.
With Cool Whip make a layer on top of the cookies in the pan.
Repeat the steps above until the cookies and cool whip are used up.
Once finished, let it sit in the refrigerator for one hour then serve.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut in small pieces.
Cook rice according to directions on package.
Saute onion and sliced water chestnuts in small amount of butter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 1 1/2 or 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese and bake 50 minutes at 300°.

title: molded orange salad
directions: Three cans of Mandarin oranges can be used in place of regular oranges.

title: egg soup
directions: Heat chicken stock or consomme to boiling.
Dribble the egg, well stirred, gradually into the stock, stirring constantly.
Add the soy sauce and salt (do not add salt if consomme is used).
Add one thinly sliced green onion.
This may be floated on the soup. Serves 2 or 3.

title: dump cake
directions: "Dump" cherry pie filling in bottom of rectangular cake pan. Layer pineapple, then dry cake mix.
Top with slices of margarine and pecans.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
In a saucepan, combine oil, margarine, peanut butter, and water, bring to a boil.
Pour hot peanut butter mixture over dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 12x18 sheet cake pan. Bake in preheated oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Mean while prepare frosting.

title: pickled okra
directions: In jars, put garlic, hot peppers and dill seed.
Pack with okra.
Bring to boil pickle salt, vinegar and water.
Pour over okra and seal.

title: cottage pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown hamburger meat and drain off the fat.
Add chopped onion and simmer 2 to 3 minutes until opaque. Add soup, mushrooms, salt and pepper; mix well and put into a casserole dish.
Spread mashed potatoes over mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese topping is light brown (and potatoes are heated through if cold mashed potatoes were used).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Let graham crackers soak in milk until soft.
Cream butter, sugar and baking powder.
Beat eggs separate; add yolks, then graham crackers, egg whites, coconut and nuts, if desired.
Put white 7 minute icing on it.
Bake two layers.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Make hamburg into patties and brown in margarine.
Place patties in bottom of greased casserole dish (3-quart).
Pare potatoes and cut into chunks.
Arrange vegetables in layers.
Add flour and salt to pan drippings and add 2 cups of water to make gravy.
Pour over vegetables/meat layers.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: ramen salad
directions: Mix diced cabbage, crumbled noodles, onions, almonds, seed and chestnuts.
Mix together packet of chicken flavoring from Ramen package, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss.
Can be made well in advance.

title: family favorite hamburger casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil a 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish. Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat.
Add onion.
Saute until softened.
Push to one side of skillet. Add meat. Saute until brown. Add green beans. Cook and stir about 5 minutes or until thawed.
Add potatoes.
Combine tomato soup and water.
Stir until well blended. Stir into skillet. Stir in basil, salt and pepper. Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat oysters in their liquor.
Add 1/4 cup margarine and seasonings.
When edges of oysters have curled, add milk that has been scalded.
Bring just to boiling, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat at once.
Additional margarine and paprika may be added to each bowl as served.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine milk and soup.
Add tuna, peas and 1 cup potato chips. Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 cup potato chips.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and toss lightly to blend well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve on crisp lettuce, if desired.
Makes 6 cups or 8 servings.

title: garden special
directions: Simmer in large pot for 20 minutes.
Bring to boil.
Put into hot jars.
Seal and pressure at 5 pounds for 15 minutes.
This can be used later with rice or with added vegetables for soup.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together flour, butter and pecans.
Spread out and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: pumpkin bars with cream cheese icing
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin together until light.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Spread batter in an ungreased 9 x 15 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool, then ice with cream cheese icing.

title: very berry compote
directions: In large bowl, gently toss strawberries with sugar; cover. Refrigerate 2 hours, tossing occasionally.
Just before serving, alternately spoon strawberries, raspberries and blueberries into large bowl.
Combine ice cream with orange peel.
Spoon some on top of berries to garnish.
Pass remainder in small bowl.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: nacho dip
directions: Melt Velveeta in slow cooker.
Add chili and salsa.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve as dip with white corn nacho chips.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Let set.
Add Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Layer pudding and crackers, ending with crackers.
Mix remaining ingredients in small bowl. Spread over dessert.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken confetti
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Season with salt and pepper. In large skillet or Dutch oven, brown chicken in oil, then remove.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons fat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir until onion is tender.
Stir chicken and remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover tightly. Cook chicken slowly 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Stir occasionally, adding water when necessary.
Skim off excess fat.
Serve on spaghetti, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve with dilled zucchini and garlic bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash until tender; drain.
Combine all ingredients except a small amount of cheese and crackers.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly (mix in blueberries by hand). Bake in loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle sugar on top.

title: corn soup(guatemala)
directions: If using fresh corn, cook it in boiling water for 5-10 minutes or until tender. Drain, keep water. Cut corn off cob. If you use canned corn, drain and keep liquid. Melt the margarine in a large saucepan and cook until onion is soft. Sprinkle in the flour, mixing well. Cook a couple of minutes, stirring constantly. Remove pan from heat and slowly pour in the milk, stirring to give a smooth consistency. Add the corn, along with salt and pepper to taste, and add about
1/2 cup of water used to boil corn. Bring soup to a gentle boil, stir as mixture thickens. Serve hot. Makes 4 cups.

title: bean dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of dish.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Spread on top of beans.
Chop onions and tomatoes and lay on top.
Pour salsa on top and shred cheese on top.
Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix good.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chunky minestrone
directions: In a Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium high heat. Cook and stir the onion, carrot and garlic in hot oil about 3 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in the undrained tomatoes, broth, water, uncooked rice and Italian seasoning. Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in the spinach, beans, zucchini and pepper. Cook, covered, for 5 minutes more. If desired, sprinkle each serving with cheese. Makes 5 (1 3/4 cups) servings.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Grease a casserole and mix the grated Cheddar cheese and Ortega chilies in bottom of casserole.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute and 25 seconds.
Remove from heat.
Add stick of butter (cut into chunks); stir until about melted.
Add vanilla, peanut butter, then oats.
Stir up very good, then drop by the spoonful onto wax paper.
Cool.
Makes about 24 cookies.

title: manicotti & stuffed shells
directions: In a large bowl, mix ricotta cheese, shredded mozzarella cheese, romano cheese, parsley, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic; set aside.

title: ham delight
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut pepper in half lengthwise and remove the core and ribs.
Flatten slightly and place on aluminum foil.
Place under the broiler until skin is charred black.
Remove to a plastic bag, seal and let steam for 10 minutes.
Slip skin off.
Reserve.

title: no-knead rolls
directions: Put 1 c. water in large bowl.
Add butter, salt, and sugar. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. water plus a pinch of sugar.
Add to the bowl with other ingredients.
Beat 1 egg and milk together and add to the bowl.
Add flour to form stiff batter.
Cover and let rise 15-20 minutes.
Divide into muffin tins or form rolls.
Makes 18 rolls in tins or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, allspice, salt and soda to first mixture.
Add vanilla, chopped apples and pecans.
Bake on sheet pan or tube pan for about 50 minutes or when toothpick comes out clean.
Bake at 300° or 325°.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Discard all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add potatoes and their sauce to pan.
Stir in water. Heat to boiling and simmer 25 minutes until potatoes are tender. Carefully stir in vinegar, bacon and bacon drippings.
Garnish with finely chopped egg.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Cool cake and break into small pieces or crumble it.
In a punch bowl or another large glass bowl, make following layers:
cake crumbs, pudding, pineapple, pie filling and Cool Whip; repeat layers.
Store in refrigerator until served.

title: "fish and chips" fish
directions: Pat fish dry.
Mix soda and vinegar.
Stir vinegar mixture and water into flour and salt mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Dip fish into batter.
Fry about 3 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well.
Stuff peppers generously with meat mixture.
Place in casserole.
If you have meat left over, roll a few meatballs to put in around the peppers.
Heat tomato soup with 1/2 can water and 1/2 can milk.
Pour over peppers and bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and a salad.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar slowly, add milk and boil for two minutes. Chill. Add powdered sugar, vanilla and salt. Beat with mixer until thick enough to spread.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cut potatoes up and put on to boil.
When they are done, take off the stove, drain water and mash potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, eggs, condensed milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into three pie crusts and cook in the oven at 350° until done.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: mrs. capp's heavenly hot fudge sauce(1961)
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler.
Add chocolate and blend. Add sugar, milk and salt and cook on low heat, stirring frequently, for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix dry pudding and Cool Whip together.
Add pineapple with juice.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Chill for a few hours and serve.

title: caramel corn
directions: In saucepan, mix butter, Karo, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add soda.
Pour caramel sauce over popped corn and stir.
Place into 3 large pans and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring several times. Store in airtight container.
Yields 8 quarts.

title: carrot rice
directions: Heat the oil.
Add the onion and saute until soft.
Add the carrots and saute.
Add the water, lower the heat and cover; cook for 7 to 10 minutes until soft.
Add the salt and the curry powder; mix.
Cook the rice separately.
When rice is ready, add the carrot onion mix to the rice.
Combine the two items slowly and serve.
Ideas:
Serve with your favorite meat dish or favorite salad.

title: pecan log
directions: Crush vanilla wafers with rolling pin or blender as fine as possible.
Add raisins and cut up dates.
Add milk and pecans. Mix well with hands until everything is moist.
Do not have any dry ingredients left in mixture.
Roll logs in powdered sugar. Wrap individual logs in Saran Wrap.
Store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 6 to 8 logs.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and flour.
Stir in water and pumpkin.
Bake in three 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pans at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: apple butter
directions: Quarter and cook apples, unpeeled, with water.
Cover, let simmer until apples are tender.
Run through sieve.
There should be about 5 quarts apple pulp.
Add half as much sugar as you have pulp.
Add spices.
Let simmer 2 hours, stirring frequently.
When thick, pour into hot jars and seal at once.
Remember, apple butter becomes thicker when cold.
Makes 9 or 10 pints.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil in saucepan.
Rinse cranberries and add to boiling liquid.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Pour immediately into container(s) and allow to cool completely before covering and placing in refrigerator.

title: italian sirloin steak
directions: Cut steak into 2 x 3-inch strips, then slice in half (thin pieces).
Tenderize with meat mallet.
Mix egg and milk.
Dip steak in batter mix, then roll in bread crumbs.
Fry at medium temperature.
Mix remaining ingredients for tomato base dressing. Heat.
Serve on the side for dipping.

title: hazel claus' candy nut rolls
directions: Cook the sugar, syrup and water to firm ball stage.
Pour 1/2 over egg whites; beat and set in pan of hot water.
Cook other 1/2 mixture to hard ball stage.
Pour over first half; beat until smooth.
Pour in pan; mark into bars when cool.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash and pick over dried beans.
Cover with cold water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Place beans with 2 quarts of hot water, onion, salt and pepper with meat in 3-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat until cover vibrates or vapors escape.
Reduce heat and cook 3 to 4 hours.

title: cookie vanilla frosting
directions: Beat until smooth.
To color, add a few drops of food coloring.

title: no-bake chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Line an 8-inch square pan with plastic wrap, letting ends extend above 2 sides of pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and milk in a medium-size bowl with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour cappuccino into a deep bowl.
Quickly dip cookies, one at a time, into the cappuccino; then spread one side with cream cheese mixture.
Arrange in lined pan as follows:
Starting from right to left, place 5 cookies, spread side down and slightly overlapping, in a row.
Place next row of cookies from left to right.
Repeat until 4 rows of cookies cover bottom of pan, wedging in last row, if needed.
Rotate pan 1/4 turn and add another layer of cookies, alternating directions of rows.
Repeat rotating pan 1/4 turn and layering 2 more times for a total of 4 layers.
Pour any remaining cappuccino over the top.

title: tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables in food chopper.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt and spices.
Pour vinegar over mixture and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
Pack into hot jars and seal.

title: omelet(serves 12)
directions: Mix together eggs, basil, salt, milk and sour cream.
Add mushrooms, green onions and Cheddar cheese.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture over butter.
Keep overnight.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, uncovered.

title: jerry's gingerbread waffles with peach sauce
directions: Combine baking mix, milk, egg, molasses and spices.
Pour 1/2 cup batter in preheated waffle iron.
Texture of cooked waffle will be cake-like.
Do not overcook or waffle will burn.
Repeat with remaining batter.

title: oven roast potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in 1-inch squares.
Place in roasting pan with oil and spices; mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat egg until light.
Stir soda into applesauce; add to creamed mixture.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Add raisins and nuts; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture.
Drop from spoon onto greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: 14 day pickles
directions: Bring to boil and pour over cucumbers.
Cover and leave 7 days.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and refrigerate.
May serve as salad or entree.
Serves 16.

title: lemon chip (drop) cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, sugar, eggs, extract and lemon rind. Sift flour, soda and salt; stir into the first mixture. Then add chopped nuts and lemon chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonful 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly and remove from cookie sheet. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: dot's salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until serving time.

title: microwave corn-on-the-cob
directions: Place ear of corn with husk in the microwave.
Cook it for 3 minutes on High.
Remove husk, butter and salt the ear.
You are ready to eat!
Two or more ears: 4 minutes.
See if they are hot.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Add to above and add 1 cup nuts.
Blend well and chill.
Drop. Bake in 400 degree oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon yogurt grilled chicken(cooking time:  about 20 minutes)
directions: In small bowl, combine yogurt, parsley, lemon juice, oil, onion, rosemary, honey, garlic and pepper.
Add salt to taste. Place chicken in shallow glass dish; brush mixture on all sides. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 3 hours or overnight.
Prepare grill by lightly greasing cooking surface of grill.
Place chicken on grill over medium-hot heat.
Cover and cook about 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until no longer pink in center, brushing occasionally with marinade (low-fat chicken).

title: sunday go to church chicken casserole
directions: Spread chipped beef in bottom of flat, greased casserole dish. Wrap each chicken breast with a piece of bacon.
Arrange chicken breast on chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over all. Refrigerate.
When ready, bake at 300° for 2 to 3 hours, uncovered. Can increase chicken breasts to 8 and bacon strips to 8 and bake at 275° for three hours.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.

Drain off grease. Add into pan the cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup, water, rice and soy sauce. Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and then 30 more minutes uncovered. Sprinkle with Chinese noodles and set back into oven for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: s'mores snack
directions: Mix and store in an airtight container.

title: mom white's refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald (not
boil)
milk,
sugar
and Crisco, then cool. Mix yeast
and
remaining
milk, sugar and Crisco mixture with flour. Set aside
and
let
rise 2 hours.
After 2 hours, add salt, baking powder and soda.
Mix more flour to knead.
Knead on board. Chill in refrigerator about 2 hours.
When ready to use, roll out.
Let
rise
and bake at 325° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
A family favorite!

title: chocolate sandwiches(cookies)
directions: Mix together. Drop by tablespoons onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Brown chops on all sides.
Place sliced apples in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter. Top with chops. Cover. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: molasses candy(a very old recipe)
directions: Melt butter in a big iron skillet, then take the 2 cups of molasses and stir in the butter.
After the mixture begins to boil, stir constantly.
Test the boiling mixture by dropping a little from a spoon into a cup of cold water.
When the candy is brittle enough, lower the heat and add the vinegar.
Stir in, then remove from heat; let cool.
This is a taffy pulled candy.
Keep pulling until it becomes light in color and becomes harder and harder to pull.
Spread on table, then with the back of knife, quickly mark the pieces into 1-inch pieces.
Then pick up candy and lightly tap in bite-size pieces.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch thoroughly.
Add water and stir until mixture dissolves.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Mixture should be thick and clear.
Remove from heat and stir in jello. Refrigerate until cool (not set).
Add strawberries and pour into shell and set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and place in the bottom of a 9-inch cake pan for the crust.

title: grilled alaskan king salmon
directions: Mix brown sugar, lemon juice, dill, butter and cayenne pepper. Brush this mixture over salmon steaks and place on grill.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Cut off stems of artichokes and across 1 inch of top leaves. Remove prickly tip of other leaves by clipping off top.
Rinse thoroughly in cold water; drain.
Press top, cut side down, firmly to force leaves to open slightly.
Pull leaves gently to open far enough to stuff.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir in milk and preserves, then the baking powder, cinnamon and flour (sifted together). Pour into waxed paper lined 8x8 inch pan or dish. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in a 350 degree oven. Yield 9 servings. Serve as a cake with warm cream if desired.

title: baked onions
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered casserole, place alternate layers of onions, potato chips and cheese.
Mix soups and milk; pour over top of layers in casserole.
Sprinkle generously with cayenne.
Bake in preheated 350° gas oven for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: If using frozen spinach, thaw and squeeze out water.
Combine all ingredients and chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours before serving.
Shredded carrot can be added for more color. Serve with raw vegetables or low fat crackers.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Wash beans and remove tips.
Add them, a handful at a time, to large pot of boiling, salted water, so that the water does not stop boiling.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes.
Then immediately drain and plunge into cold water to stop the cooking.
Return beans to empty pot and shake briefly over high heat to dry them. Set aside and keep warm.
Melt butter in the oil and saute mushrooms until just wilted.
Combine with beans; toss and season well.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour into pie crust. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and powdered sugar.
Beat in egg and add flour, cream of tartar, soda and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in roaster and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.

title: moms oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla. Mix together water, soda and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 400 degrees for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: jello pie
directions: Mix pineapple juice, sugar and egg.
Let come to a boil; remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Beat milk until soft peaks form and mix with Jell-O mixture.
Pour into a baked pie shell. Refrigerate until set.

title: ground beef barbecue
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.
Freezes well or may be kept in refrigerator for 10 days.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Pour in remaining ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 425° until brown.
Save remaining dough in refrigerator for later.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, then molasses. Mix well. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together; mix in. Last, add the boiling water, very slowly, stirring constantly. Bake in a shallow greased pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked cranberry sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 cups.

title: shrimp and broccoli casserole
directions: Make a sauce with margarine, flour, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in 1 cup cheese.
In greased 2-quart casserole, layer broccoli, rice, shrimp and mushrooms.
pour sauce over casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake yellow cake.
Mix instant pudding and cream cheese together, then put on cooled cake, then add pineapple and whipped cream.

title: oatmeal coconut drop cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Stir and add 1/2 to 2/3 cup water; cook until thick.
Add potatoes and onions.
Put in casserole dish and heat.
This can be made ahead of time and will keep in refrigerator several days. Makes 2 small casseroles.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Bake chocolate cake; cool.
Mix instant pudding according to recipe.
Break 1/3 of cake into small pieces and put in a large bowl.
Then add 1/3 of the pudding and 1/3 of the Cool Whip and some toffee bits.
Continue to layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip and toffee bits.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in frozen berries. Break up cranberry sauce with a fork; stir into mixture.
Chill until partially set.
Carefully pour in soda.
Stir gently.
Pour into a 6-cup ring mold.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.
Turn mold onto crisp lettuce leaves.

title: spaghetti squash bake
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
In a skillet, saute oil, peppers, onion, mushrooms, garlic, red wine vinegar, squash and seasoning until tender.
Add tomato sauce and paste; simmer 10 minutes in a greased baking dish.
Add layers spaghetti, sauce, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: steak-umm
directions: Two sandwiches use 4 Steak-umms.
Cook Steak-umms over medium heat until brown or done.
Mix pepper, onion and mushrooms in with Steak-umms.
Cover with slices of Swiss cheese until melted.
Add other ingredients as you would like to sandwich.

title: pina colada cake
directions: *Prepare cake mix according to package directions and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan, top poked with a fork.

title: pearl's congealed salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello straight from package. Pour in buttermilk and stir together.
When cool, add Cool Whip. Fold in nuts.
Pour into long pan to set.

title: popovers
directions: Mix; bake in well buttered muffin tins in a quick oven.
This recipe takes no baking powder.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with a mixture of 1/2 cups sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Press with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen small cookies.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Wash chicken and pat dry.
In oven melt shortening and butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken in egg; then roll into flour mixture.
Place chicken, skin side down in melted shortening. Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and cook 30 minutes longer or until thickest pieces are done.

title: chicken atop rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine uncooked rice, mushrooms, celery, onion, chicken soup and water.
Arrange chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with salt.
Brush or drizzle chicken with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika and poultry seasoning.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend together the sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Stir in egg yolks (beaten lightly), butter and milk.
Beat egg whites stiff and slowly blend into the mixture.
Pour in 10-inch pie shell and bake in a 325° oven.

title: anti-cancer marinade for meat
directions: In a glass dish, mix ingredients.
Put meat in a closeable plastic bag.
Cover with marinade.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: black bean dip
directions: Puree beans, add remaining ingredients and blend.
Serve with sliced garden veggies &/or tortilla chips

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except bread in blender.
Pour into baking dish.
Break up bread and place on top. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: karen long's nut roll
directions: Beat flour, Crisco and salt together.
Put yeast mixture and eggs all together and mix.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, let it set out for about 10 minutes.
Put dough into balls the size of a bun.
Roll out each to an oblong shape.
Spread with nut filling and roll up like a jelly roll.
Bake 20 minutes in oven at 350° or until golden brown.
Makes 3 or 4 rolls.

title: grilled new potatoes
directions: Preheat grill or broiler.
Spray a large piece of heavy-duty foil generously with cooking spray.
Arrange onion slices in center of foil.
Cut potatoes into halves; arrange cut sides up on onion slices.
Drizzle butter over potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic salt and rosemary.
Fold foil to enclose vegetables and seal tightly.
Grill or broil for 40 minutes, turning once. Open foil and fold back edges.
Grill for additional 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Transfer to a serving dish.

title: delmonico potatoes
directions: Cook, peel and dice potatoes.
Place in buttered casserole. Melt butter in saucepan, add flour, milk and pepper, making a white sauce.
Pour sauce over potatoes after putting some of the cheese throughout the potatoes.
Place remainder of cheese on top. May sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one pan meal deal for the jury
directions: Start with sliced sausage.
Cut them bite size.
Brown sausage in large skillet.
Add onion and saute with sausage.
Add peas and water; stir.
Add rice.
Stir.
Cover pan with lid.
Stir occasionally.
With heat turned very low, simmer approximately 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
The batter will be lumpy.
Bake at 350° for about an hour.

title: brownies
directions: First put hot butter melted from microwave in it.
You have to put black stuff in the eggs and oil.
Then stir it with a wierd thing and hold on to it. Put two scoops of water.
A bag of flour gets dumped in it.
Put it in the oven.
Turns into brownies. It has chocolate and frosting on top.

title: loretta's mississippi muds
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil for 2 minutes.
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
(To become firm in 15 minutes, do not refrigerate.)

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together, drain.
Fry bacon, reserve fat.
Mix all ingredients together, including bacon fat. (Taste, if too bland add small amounts of granulated sugar or barbecue sauce until just right.)
Place in crock-pot on low heat. Cook at least 3 hours.
Delicious!

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt until smooth. Slowly blend in milk; stir until thickened.
Stir in cheese. Serve over steamed broccoli or cauliflower.

title: favorite oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs (beaten), water and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in oatmeal, nuts and chocolate chips or raisins.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pineapple apricot salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Pour into a bowl and add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Fold in remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over top with chopped pecans. Chill until firm.

title: tasty potato casserole
directions: Boil, cook and coarsely grate potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, except 3 tablespoons butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Top with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Bake until bubbly and heated through, approximately 45 minutes at 350°. May be made ahead and refrigerated or frozen until cooking time.
If frozen, defrost before baking.
Serves 8.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Whip the cream cheese. Add eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pilgrim's pie
directions: In large bowl, mix ground meat, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt; mix well.
Pat down in pie pan.
Drain corn and put on top.
Make potatoes; add on top of corn.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (drain grease if any).

title: peanut salad
directions: Prepare
peanuts
in
the food processor until they are finely crushed; set aside 2 tablespoons to sprinkle on the top of finished
salad.
Mix with oleo and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch flat dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.	Set aside to cool.
Mix 1/2 cup of Cool Whip with cream cheese and sugar. Spread
over
cool	peanuts.
Take	liquid from strawberries
and pineapple.	If not 2 cups, add water to make it. Add
jello to liquid and boil for 2 minutes.
Let this mixture nearly
set.
Add the
fruit.
Spread over the peanut mixture and
top
with
rest of Cool Whip and sprinkle peanuts on the top.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes. Add the lemon jello and the softened cream cheese.
Cool thoroughly.
Add the chopped celery, apple, nuts and Cool Whip. Spread in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Chill overnight.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Cook about 4 hours or until tender.
Serve with corn bread.

title: texas pie
directions: Place pie filling in 9x13 Pyrex. Top with pineapple. Do not stir. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over filling. Sprinkle coconut and pecans over cake mix. Pour melted margarine over all. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Takes only one pan.

title: gigi's rice pudding(kindergarten recipe)
directions: *My jobs.
Mommy or Daddy has to help in this recipe.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (will be very thin).
Cook 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: sauerbraten burgers
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons of gingersnaps.
Mix remaining gingersnaps with 2 tablespoons of tomato sauce, onion, raisins and salt.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into 4 (3/4-inch) patties. Brown in skillet and drain.
Combine remaining items and pour over burgers.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, spooning sauce on meat. Remove burgers.
Stir in remaining gingersnaps into sauce.
Cook until bubbly.
Skim off fat.
Pour over burgers.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and use 1/3 cup per cup of hot water.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Blend all together in blender (mixer may be used) until smooth.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean.

title: frank veggie hot pot
directions: Cut franks into 1 inch pieces.
Heat to boiling broth and water; add macaroni, basil, salt and black pepper.
Return to boil; cook uncovered for 5 minutes.
Stir in franks, vegetables and onions.
Simmer 5 minutes longer, until macaroni is tender, vegetables are cooked and water is almost all absorbed.
Fold in sour cream and mayonnaise.
Garnish with chopped parsley, chives or green pepper before serving.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Put raw meat in casserole.
Top with soup.
Add Tater Tots on top of the soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together in a very large bowl meat, soups and tomatoes. (This part can be done ahead of time and left in refrigerator, even overnight.)
Carefully fold in the chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until good and hot and cheese is melted.

title: diet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Drain crushed pineapple, reserving juice.
Sprinkle brown sugar onto bottom of pan.
Top with an even layer of crushed pineapple. Slice cherries in half; arrange, cut side up, in pan.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix applesauce, sugar, reserved pineapple juice and egg whites.
Add flour mixture; mix just to blend.
Gently pour batter over pineapple.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto serving dish and cool completely. Makes 8 servings.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Simmer for 8 minutes. Strain; pour over eggs along with beet juice for color.
Store in refrigerator for several days.

title: new orleans beignets
directions: In saucepan over medium heat, combine water, butter, sugar and dash of salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring, until butter melts.
Add flour all at once.
Over low heat, cook and stir until mixture forms into a ball.
Remove from heat.
Vigorously beat in eggs, one at a time, until mixture is smooth and shiny.
Add vanilla, mixing well.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with Pam cooking spray.

title: dill salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Use over salads or raw vegetables.

title: nutty noodly clusters
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine chocolate and butterscotch chips. Melt, stirring constantly, over low heat.
Remove from heat and stir in the La Choy noodles and nuts.
Mix quickly to coat evenly. Dip out by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and cool.
Makes 24 nutty noodly clusters.

title: corn stuffed pork chops
directions: Mix corn with liquid, bread cubes, onion, salt and sage. Stuff pork chop pockets with mixture.
Fry pork chops in shortening until brown, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until pork chops are done, about 1 hour.

title: moon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter, add egg yolks, and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add lemon juice.
Mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into greased and floured jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 25 - 30 minutes.
When cool sprinkle with powdered sugar (sifted).
Cut into moon shapes using small glass cutting 1/2 of cake to look like crescent moon.

title: turkey rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large kettle over medium heat. Saute onion, pepper, celery and mushrooms until tender-crisp.
Stir in flour. Do not brown.
Slowly add broth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Stir in rice and half and half.
Heat to serving temperature. Blend in salt, pepper and vermouth.
(Good way to use up last of Thanksgiving turkey.)
I boil up all the bones and make my broth, plus the meat.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small florets; cut grapes in half if large. Put all ingredients into mixing bowl.

title: candy shop pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in 1 cup white chocolate chips. Spread batter in lightly greased 12 to 14-inch pizza pan or 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 24 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pizza batter bread
directions: In mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour, the yeast, oregano and garlic powder.
In saucepan, heat water, butter or margarine, sugar and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring to melt butter.
Add to dry mixture in mixer bowl.

title: black-bottom pie
directions: Combine the 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and beaten egg yolks. Slowly add to scalded milk.
Cook and stir in double boiler (or heavy pan) until custard coats a spoon.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
To 1 cup of the custard, add the chocolate pieces and stir until melted.
Pour into bottom of cooled, baked pastry shell. Chill.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place meat in a deep pot.
Cover with cold water.
Cover and simmer gently for 3 to 4 hours or until fork-tender.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions about 30 minutes before end of cooking time. Add cabbage according to degree of doneness you like.
Remove meat to cutting board and let set at least 15 minutes before slicing. (Make very thin slices.)
Serves 8.

title: lawry's chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Yummy!

title: chicken with wild rice(from a friend, holly)
directions: Boil
chicken
with
water, sherry, salt, onion, celery and curry
powder
1/2 hours.
Cool and debone.
Cook rice using water from chicken.
Saute mushrooms in 1/4 cup butter. Mix
soup, sour cream, chicken and rice together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with whole mushrooms. This is
a great buffet dish and always a big hit.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cappuccino pie
directions: Pour the milk into a medium bowl.
Add the pudding mixes, coffee and half of the whipped topping.
Whisk for 1 minute (the mixture will be thick).
Pour into the pie shell.
Spread the remaining whipped topping over the top.
Chill until serving time. Serves 8.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Melt butter in 1/4 cup boiling water.
Add flour and dash of salt; stir vigorously.
Cook and stir until mixture forms a ball that doesn't separate.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add egg and beat vigorously until smooth.
Stir in cheese.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix beans, rice, Fritos and spices in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: caramel oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease 13 x 9 baking pan.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
Add margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup oats mixture for topping; press remaining mixture in bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 minutes; remove from oven.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter over low heat in top of double boiler.
Stir in flour, lobster, nutmeg, paprika, salt and sherry.
Beat yolks lightly in small bowl.
Add cream; mix well.
Slowly stir yolk mixture into the lobster.
Cook over hot water, stirring, until just thickened.
Serve over toast or shells.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cashew beef with snowpeas
directions: Brown cubed beef in the oil in a large casserole or dutch oven.
Add soy sauce and broth and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 20-30 minutes.
If you like a thicker sauce, mix 1/2 cup cornstarch to 1/3 cup cold water and stir into beef, cook for about 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet over medium heat, melt 1/4 cup butter and add celery, pepper, onion and carrots, cook until vegetables are tender.
Add snowpeas and warm through-add vegetables to the beef mixture.
Serve over fried rice topped with 1 cup sliced, toasted cashews.

title: quiche
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell.

title: spiced glazed pecans
directions: Lightly toast pecans in oven.
Combine vanilla, cinnamon, salt, sugar and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil without stirring to soft ball stage.
Add pecans.
Stir until pecans are coated.
Spread on waxed paper.
Separate into individual pieces.

title: creamy chicken and nuggets
directions: Beat the eggs slightly in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pack mixture into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes. Unmold onto hot platter.
Garnish with parsley and hard-cooked egg segments.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sauerkraut and meat
directions: Cook bacon until brown, drain.
Saute onion in bacon drippings.
Add kraut and bacon mix. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat water, dissolve sugar, bouillon and caraway seed.
Pour over kraut.
Add meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel and cut up tomatoes, onion and hot pepper.
Add other ingredients and cook about 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: ultra low-fat baked sweet and sour chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine marmalade, onion soup mix, soy sauce, orange juice and Italian dressing.
Spray large pan or dish with Pam buttery nonstick cooking spray.
Place chicken breasts in pan and pour sauce over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Entire recipe makes 8 servings.
Grams of fat per serving, 1; calories per serving, 178.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut uncooked bacon slices in half. Wrap each half slice of bacon around water chestnut. Insert toothpick to secure.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove and drain grease.
Mix mayonnaise, brown sugar and chili sauce.
Pour over bacon roll-ups.
Bake an additional 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: delicious dream salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole or put into individual cups.
Leave in freezer until ready to serve.
Unmold individual cups and place on top of lettuce leaf.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add juice of oranges and sherbet.
Cool until it starts to set.
Fold in whipped cream and oranges.
Pour into mold.
Chill until serving time.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Thaw out potatoes; mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes and butter mixed. Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Let thaw to slush and serve.

title: roquefort pecan canapes
directions: Microwave cheese, uncovered, at Low for 30 seconds to 1 minute, until soft.
Blend in Roquefort and 1/2 the chopped nuts (1/4 cup), Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard and paprika.
Combine thoroughly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll the biscuit quarters in this mixture and arrange in an angel food cake pan that has been greased.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add molasses and mix thoroughly.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift flour with spices, salt and baking powder.
Mix flour mixture into butter mixture. Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Form into 1 inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes or until cookies just start to darken.

title: sally's hot dills
directions: Drain and rinse pickles.
Slice lengthwise or crosswise.
In glass or Pyrex bowl (large), place one layer of pickles, 1 crushed cinnamon stick, 1 tablespoon pickling spice, 1 tablespoon crushed red pepper and 1 cup sugar.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
Pour over 1 cup apple cider vinegar.
Do not stir!
Cover with Saran Wrap and leave out at room temperature. Stir once each day, next 3 days.
Replace in same jar, well washed and cap with original lid. Keep in refrigerator.

title: janice's chocolate candy
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, marshmallows and milk in heavy saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil and boil 6 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips and pecans. Stir until melted. Pour into buttered oblong pan. When cool, cut into squares.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour. About 30 minutes into baking time, mix 1/4 to 1/2 cup catsup, 1 tablespoon mustard and 2 tablespoons brown sugar; pour over top of meat loaf and continue cooking another 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: sauce for strawberries
directions: Mix together all ingredients and enjoy.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar, Karo and salt in an iron skillet (only).
When this begins to boil, stirring constantly, add 1 cup raw Spanish peanuts.
Continue to stir until nuts begin to crack and pop.
The syrup begins to look slightly caramel and nuts smell roasted.
Do not overcook or nuts will taste burnt.
Cook from 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and fold in vanilla and soda.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour out and spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and break.

title: ham loaffort morgan, colorado
directions: Place 7 lbs. of pork, cut in small chunks, in large kettle.

title: three bean bake(alida beans)
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion, in that order.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Add other ingredients, stirring frequently.
Cook on low heat until warm.
Serve over chips with grated cheese on top.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in an airtight container.
For 1 serving, add boiling water to 2 teaspoons mix.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Cream together for 5 minutes the eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin. Add flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. Mix well.
Spread on large ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes. Frost and cut into squares.

title: easy green bean and rice salad for a crowd
directions: Prepare this one day ahead of time.

title: beef and vegetable soup
directions: Coat stew beef with flour.
Brown in cooking oil in large skillet or Dutch oven.
Drain fat.
Add beef stew seasoning mix, garlic salt and water.
Cover, simmer until almost tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in pressure cooker and cook for 15 minutes.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown stew beef in big pot.
Add 3 to 4 cups water.
Add dry onion soup mix; cook until tender.
Add whole potatoes, carrots, celery and cabbage (cut into pieces and stalk removed).
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Serve with corn bread.

title: tuna and cheese on a bun
directions: Mix all together. Put on bun. Add the slice of cheese. Wrap in foil on a pan. Bake in 300° oven just enough to heat or melt the cheese.

title: potato casserole brunch or side dish
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine with butter in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion, soup, sour cream and cheese. Blend thoroughly.
Pour in buttered casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: potatoes in beef jackets
directions: Cook potatoes in skins until almost tender and then remove skins.
Mix ground beef, egg, salt and pepper.
Cover each potato with hamburger, pressing well.
Place balls in greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour tomato juice over balls and top with onions and peppers.
Bake at 350° until meat is done and potatoes tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible carrot pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Mix carrots, rice, cheese, onion and basil; spread in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth; 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: breakfast cake
directions: Mix until crumbs and set aside for top of cake.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions. In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp. Crumble and set aside.

Drain off fat. Add sausage, garlic and parsley. Cook sausage until done. Stir in tomatoes and bacon. Mix with spaghetti. Quickly scramble eggs. Add eggs and remaining ingredients to spaghetti. Toss lightly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: coquito(native drink from st. croix, usvi)
directions: Break open one dried coconut with hammer.
Remove meat from shell.
Wash and grate on coarse side of grater.
Combine coconut and rum in a large pot.
Toss with a cup to remove milk.
Squeeze through a clean, grease-free cheesecloth (throw away the coconut). Add eggs and mix well.
Boil cinnamon, cloves and water for 20 minutes on high heat (a strong blend is required and additional water may be added to make 2 cups).
Cool completely.
Add to milk.
Sweeten with sugar.
Pour into sterile, translucent rum bottles.
Chill before serving or pour over ice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: super-easy fruit dip
directions: Mix both ingredients together until smooth.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite fruits.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to cream mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Then spread 1/2 dough in cookie sheet.
Save other half for over top.

title: chow chow
directions: Put in large container (ice chest).
Pour water over top of vegetables.
Put in 10 level tablespoons pickling salt and let set for 2 hours.
Squeeze out water.
Put vegetables in pot with vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil and put in jars with lids.
The jars will seal themselves.

title: martha's dirt delight
directions: Mix dry jello with drained cottage cheese.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: four layer pudding cake
directions: Melt margarine; add nuts and flour.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan to form crust.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Brown bread cubes in butter over medium heat.
Cook broccoli; drain and place in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Place chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayo, milk, cheese and lemon juice. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with portable electric mixer, beat butter with sugar until well blended.
Beat in egg yolks until blended.
Blend in flour and milk; stir in lemon peel and lemon juice.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised.
Using a wire whisk or rubber scraper, fold egg whites into lemon mixture.
Turn mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set casserole in pan containing 1-inch boiling water.
Bake for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until golden brown and silver knife inserted 1-inch from center comes out clean.
Let stand for 30 minutes before serving.
Serve warm, with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as directed.
Mix together all ingredients into well-drained spinach.
Spinach mixture needs to hold together, not runny.
Add more croutons if it seems to moist.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain kidney beans.
Combine kidney beans with remaining ingredients and chill.
Salad can be garnished with bacon bits or grated cheese.

title: thanksgiving baked beans
directions: Pour sauce off top of pork and beans; save sauce. Combine sauce with rest of ingredients. Put baked beans in Corningware dish and combine with mixture. Cover and bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil 1 pound raisins slowly in water or coffee.
Allow to cool.
Add sugar and shortening.
Sift together salt, cinnamon, cloves, baking powder, soda and flour.
Add to raisin mixture.
Can add your choice of nuts also.
Bake on large cookie sheet at 350° for about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Great with Cool Whip topping.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Use cereals such as Chex, Crispix, Raisin Squares, Apple Jacks, Cinnamon Squares, etc. Any combination. The more variety; the better. Pretzel sticks or small twists, corn nuts, mixed nuts, peanuts, pecans, gold fish crackers, any variety. Pour all the cereal and nuts in large roaster pan. Heat the remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Pour over cereals. Stir. Heat in 250-degree oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Bake until dry and crispy.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix together cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle mixture on cake, then pour the other half of mix over cake.
Bake at 300° for about 50 minutes.

title: nana's american chop suey
directions: Chop and fry onion and pepper; add hamburg and brown.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour or more. Mix with cooked elbow noodles.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, margarine and vanilla until smooth.
Then add vanilla instant pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip. Mix until thickened.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Split the biscuits in half and butter each half.
Place a layer of biscuits on bottom of a large baking dish.
Add tomatoes and sprinkle with salt, pepper and sugar.
Add layers of biscuits, salt, pepper and sugar until all have been used.
Finish with tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 package of hash browns.
In a bowl, mix soup, sour cream, milk and onion.
Pour half of this mixture over hash browns.
Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese on top.
Repeat for second layer.
Cover with crushed corn flakes.
Pour 2 tablespoons of melted butter over mixture.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese snacks
directions: Cook sausage and mix with cheese spread.
Spread on opened, buttered English muffins.
Freeze on cookie sheet, then wrap individually.
Cook frozen at 325° to 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into three sections; discard wing tips. Place wings in a large resealable heavy-duty plastic bag or 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: crispy banana pudding
directions: Mix coconut, sugar and flour. Add soft oleo and bake on cookie sheet until light brown at 300 degrees. Stir often and don't let burn, cool. Spread 1/2 of crumb mixture on bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Prepare pudding according to package directions. Then spread half of pudding onto crumbs. Then slice half of bananas on pudding, then half of whipped topping. Repeat second layer as first.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over the dough and apples.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake for 30 minutes or until apples are done.

title: chicken
directions: Take chicken breast
(or
mixed parts), unseasoned, and wrap each piece of chicken in a strip of bacon.	Place chicken in a large shallow pan
or
baking dish lined with dried beef. Pour sauce over the
breasts
or other pieces of chicken.
The sauce is made of sour
cream
and soups.
Cover loosely with a sheet of foil and bake
about
hours
in	a 350° oven.
Can serve over rice.

title: stir-fry
directions: Place cooking oil in frypan; stir-fry cut up chicken and set aside.
Stir-fry all vegetables; then add chicken pieces.
Make spaghetti noodles, then put stir-fry over noodles and add Italian dressing.
Serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in oil and add mushroom soup, tomato and chicken. Make layer of Fritos and chicken, etc., ending with chicken mixture.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven until bubbles at 350°.

title: potato casserole(serves 8)
directions: Thaw potatoes about 30 minutes. Mix all ingredients in a large casserole (9 x 13 size). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's bread
directions: Stir sugar in water; sprinkle yeast on water.
Let stand until dissolved.
Stir in salt, shortening and flour until dough is stiff and not sticky.
Works best with heavy-duty mixer and dough hook. If mixed by hand, turn onto floured surface and knead well.
Turn into greased bowl, coating all sides.
Cover and let sit in warm place until doubled.
Turn out on floured surface; knead and make into rolls.
Dip in melted butter.
Place in pan and let sit until they rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Sprinkle sugar, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon on apples.
Add apples and cold water only if it looks like the apples are cooking dry, otherwise omit water.
Add butter here and there in bits. Bake at 350° 1 hour or until apples appear done.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Combine orange juice and grated rind with well beaten egg.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients, mixing just enough to dampen. Carefully fold in chopped nuts and cranberries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Spread corners and sides slightly higher than center.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour, until crust is golden brown and toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool.
Store overnight for easy slicing.

title: exciting cake
directions: Prepare cake and let
cool.
Prepare
gelatin according to package and let cool at room
temperature.
It
should
be warm, but not set.
Use fork to poke holes all over the top of cake. Pour gelatin over the top of cake so that it soaks into the holes. Refrigerate
cake
until
gelatin
sets.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: onion rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 2 1/2 cups flour and the yeast. In saucepan, heat together the milk, sugar, 2 tablespoons instant minced onion, cooking oil, mustard, salt and pepper, just until warm, stirring occasionally.
Add to dry mixture in mixer bowl. Add egg.
Beat at low speed for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately stiff dough.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, Karo and other ingredients.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 375° until firm. Test with toothpick, if it comes out clean pie is done.

title: no-cook noodle lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce to beef. Mix eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup of shredded cheese.
Add oregano to egg mixture and mix well.
Place 3 noodles in
dish;
layer
with
1 1/3 cups meat mixture, then half egg-cheese
mixture.
Top with 3 more noodles.
Pour hot water around
all edges of dish.
Cover with
foil.
Bake
at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle remaining cheese
on top.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: crab gumbo
