directions: In 3 quart saucepan cook onion in butter or margarine till tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, chicken broth, sugar, pepper, and bay leaf.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Add okra, and crab or shrimp; heat through.
Serve gumbo over hot cooked rice in soup plates.
Serves 6.

title: yankee crock roast
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 12 hours or on medium for 8 hours.

title: pork chop 'n potato bake
directions: Brown chops; sprinkle with salt.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange pork chops over this.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: cottage cheese herb dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Whirl to blend. Refrigerate several hours or overnight to bring out best flavor. Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: blender gazpacho
directions: Blend together 2 to 3 minutes cucumbers, tomatoes, consomme or water and pimiento.
Add and blend for a shorter time the olive oil.
Add, but do not blend, as the flavor would be too strong the chopped chives.
Season to taste.
Serve by pouring the broth over 2 ice cubes.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until serving.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Add milk, apple, nuts and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Cool before cutting.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine dry cake mix, dry instant pudding and 1/2 cup sugar, stirring with a wire whisk to remove large lumps.
Add oil and next 3 ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Stir in chocolate morsels.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester is clean.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: german apple pancakes
directions: Spray an ovenproof glass
casserole dish with Pam.
Mix the apples, sugar, applesauce and spices.
Spread in glass casserole dish.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes to partially cook the apples.

title: apple pineapple salad
directions: Heat butter and lemon juice until butter is melted. In a bowl combine cornstarch and water until smooth. Stir in pineapple juice from can. Bring to boil. Add sugar; cool. Combine pineapple, apples, and grapes; add dressing. Cover and chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium sized bowl until creamy.
Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: hunter's "one pot" dinner
directions: Brown beef, drain and place beef in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add everything to crock-pot.
Stir together. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 9 hours in crock-pot.

title: pumpkin swirl bread
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine the next 5 ingredients.
Mix the rest of the ingredients with dry ingredients just until moistened.
Reserve 2 cups pumpkin batter. Pour rest into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over pumpkin batter in loaf pan and top off with reserved pumpkin batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for swirl effect.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clear.
Cool 5 minutes and then remove from pan.

title: quick barbecue pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Squeeze a little lemon juice over pork chops.
Put 1 tablespoon brown sugar on each chop.
Take the half cup of ketchup and 1/2 cup water and mix well.
Pour over chops.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until done at 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, salt and milk to form soft ball stage.
Add butter; allow to cool.
Add vanilla; beat until set.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli and scallions into small pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar, raisins, vinegar and nuts.
Pour mixture over broccoli and scallions; mix well.
Cook 10 slices of bacon very crisp.
Add bacon just before serving and toss.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute first five ingredients slowly in butter or sweet oil until light brown.
Then add slowly shrimp, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer one hour and serve over cooked rice.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, peanut butter and egg together.
Roll into balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Dip bottom of small glass into sugar and press on ball to flatten into round cookie shape. Repeat with each ball.
Each cookie may be topped with chocolate star or crisscrossed with fork tines.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spinach-black bean lasagna(vegetarian)
directions: Stir together first five ingredients and 1 c. Monterey Jack cheese; set aside. Mash beans with potato masher in a large bowl; stir in pasta sauce and cumin. Spread one third of bean mixture on bottom of a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Layer with three noodles, half of spinach mixture and one cup Monterey Jack cheese; repeat layers. Spread with one third bean mixture; top with remaining three noodles and remaining bean mixture. Bake covered at 350° for one hour; uncover and top with remaining Monterey Jack cheese. Bake five more minutes or until cheese melts. Garnish if desired. Serves 6. Recipe may be doubled and baked as directed.
tags: shredded Monterey Jack cheese with peppers

title: pascha (easter bread)
directions: Scald milk. While still hot, add the butter and let cool until lukewarm. Dissolve the yeast in warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar. Add the sugar and salt to the cooled milk and slightly beaten eggs. Add mace. Put the sifted flour in bowl (7 cups) and add the yeast mixture and milk mixture. Beat until comes out smooth, then add another 3 cups flour gradually as much as is need to make soft dough. Knead until smooth and elastic. Put in greased bowl and cover. Let raise until double in bulk (2 to 3 hours). Punch down and let raise again until double in bulk. Makes 6 small and 4 large balls of dough to make the bread OR however number of loaves you wish. Pat out plain dough and about 2-inches from edge, make an indentation to look like a hat. Take the cheese mixture and put on the plain dough. Seal the cheese mix in the middle of the dough. Prick with a fork to let out air bubbles. Braid some of the dough and place in a circle around the top edge of the bread (before baking). Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken in wine sauce a la montessori
directions: Dip chicken in egg and roll in crumbs.
Fry until brown. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Saute mushrooms; add broth and sherry.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over chicken and cover with Mozzarella cheese slices.
Cover chicken with gravy and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: 7 day sweet pickles
directions: Day 1:
Slice cukes into gallon jar.
Add 1 cup canning salt. Pour boiling water over to cover.

title: tomato and zucchini soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in a large saucepan.
Stir in zucchini; saute for about 2 minutes.
Add tomato juice, chicken broth, chopped parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and sugar; heat until boils.
Cover and simmer.

title: pineapple dip
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Do not use electric mixer.
For attractive dish, half a fresh pineapple and fill inside of pineapple half with dip.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine beans and corn in greased casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients (except crackers and butter) and pour over butter and corn.

title: corn dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
In a large bowl, mix remaining ingredients well.
Add onion and celery. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan or dish (you might want to spray with Pam).
You can also dribble butter or turkey broth over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until desired doneness.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies in half and put them in the bottom of the cake pan.
Spread drained crushed pineapple on top.
Mix the pudding as the directions on the box and spread on top of pineapple.
Slice bananas on top of pudding.	Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla and coloring; add eggs. Beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and cocoa.
Sift three times.
Mix dry ingredients with creamed mixture along with milk. Dissolve soda with vinegar.
Fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Add Veg-All, both soups, onion and Ro-Tel.
Cook rice and then add to ingredients.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: swiss whipped cream - nut loaf
directions: Beat the cream until very soft peaks are formed; beat in the egg and sugar until thoroughly blended.
Mix in the grated peel, nuts and raisins.
Blend the flour, baking powder and salt; fold into the cream-sugar mixture.
Turn batter in a greased (bottom only) 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 70 minutes or until done.
Cool bread 15 minutes in pan on wire rack; remove from pan and cool completely.

title: fluffy meat loaf
directions: Pack into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 - 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: basil garlic butter
directions: Process butter and garlic cloves in a blender or food processor until smooth.
Add the basil leaves and pulse 3 to 4 times or until basil is finely chopped.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 week.
If desired, shape butter into a log; wrap in wax paper and chill.
When firm slice into smaller rounds and freeze.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
with onion.
Fry onion.
Drain liquid from beans.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.	Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Strain oysters and reserve liquid.
Add cold water to oyster liquid.
Melt 8 tablespoons butter in skillet, add onions and saute until onion is dark brown (not burned), stirring frequently. Add celery and bell peppers; cook 5 minutes.
Combine seasonings; add to vegetable mixture and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes. Add remaining butter and bay leaves.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Stir in reserved oyster liquid and water; cook 10 minutes.
Stir in bread crumbs to make moist but not runny dressing.
Remove from heat; add drained oysters.
Spoon into baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Batter will be stiff.
Knead lightly on floured board.
Place in greased bowl; cover.
Let rise 1 hour in warm, draft-free area.

Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Spread soft butter over dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Shape into roll, pinch edge to seal and cut into 1/2-inch lengths. Place, cut side up, in greased baking pan.
Cover and let rise again for 1 hour.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with buttercream frosting.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: tofu pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling
water in bowl.
Cool in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
In another bowl, mix tofu until smooth with mixer or blender.
Add lemon juice and thickened Jell-O and half of Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Use remaining Cool Whip to top the Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan and heat; serve with favorite meat.

title: spanish rice
directions: Melt butter and cook onions, celery, green pepper until soft. Stir in rice, add remaining ingredients.
Simmer covered for 20 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and sprinkle coconut in bottom of the pan. Sprinkle pecans on top of this; pour cake mix over this.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 stick butter until creamy.
By the spoonful, blob on top of the cake mix. Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cornmeal custard
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and salt to a boil, stirring continuously.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chips, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into a greased pan and chill until firm.

title: taco ring
directions: Brown ground beef; drain. Add seasoning.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour that has been sifted with salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg along with the buttermilk with soda.
When mixed well, I add prunes and nuts last.
Spray a tube pan with Pam and bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Cool.
Gets better after several days.
Can be frozen.

title: sauerkraut bake
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon over medium heat until crisp. Drain on paper towel. Crumble and set aside.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: To use a fresh pumpkin, cut it in half and remove the seeds. Place cut sides up in a large pan with sides.
Lay a piece of foil over each (loosely).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until pumpkin feels soft.
Remove pumpkin halves from the oven; scoop out the middles and use in your favorite recipe.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water (salted) and drain. Rinse in cold water. Cook onion and pepper in oleo until tender. Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimiento, milk and basil. Lay 1/2 of noodles in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam or greased. Top with 1/2 each sauce, cottage cheese, chicken and both cheeses; repeat layers, except cheeses. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Top with other cheese and bake 2 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cook cake in 9 x 13-inch dish as directed.
When finished, while hot, punch holes and pour Eagle Brand milk.
While still warm, spread caramel topping.
Let cool.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook until thick.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large casserole dish, place a layer of potatoes; dot with margarine and cheese chunks.
Sprinkle flour, onion, salt and pepper.
Add another layer of potatoes and repeat the process until all potatoes are used.
Pour milk until the casserole dish is half full.
Bake at 350° for one and one-half hours.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle with paprika and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes or until set. Can be mixed the day before and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: pecan roll
directions: Crush wafers and mix with chopped pecans.
Add milk and combine well.
Shape this mixture into a roll about 1 1/2-inches. Roll and roll up in wax paper and refrigerate for several hours. Slice before serving.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Drain liquid from salmon and reserve.
Add remaining ingredients, except last two.
Sprinkle layers of crumbs over bottom of pan and around sides of buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Spoon in salmon mixture.
Dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top and dot with remaining butter.
Bake in hot oven (400°) about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peach bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 8 1/2-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Bring a medium saucepan of water to a boil over high heat.
Add peaches and blanch for 30 to 45 seconds. Remove the peaches to a colander and cool under cold running water to stop the cooking.
Set aside.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, melted oleo and sugar.
Remove 1 cup and pat remainder into greased 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust. Spoon ice cream over crust and freeze.
Boil sugar, chocolate chips, milk and 1/2 cup oleo for 8 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Pour cooled sauce over ice cream.
Sprinkle with peanuts and spread Cool Whip on mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and onion.
Add egg; gradually beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot oil where fish was fried.
Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towel.
Serve hot with fish.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Fold together all ingredients except egg whites, then fold in egg whites. Spread in flat buttered casserole. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: savory cauliflower
directions: Place cauliflower in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole dish with 1/4 to 1/2 cup water. Cover and cook on High power for 8 to 13 minutes. Drain. Mix mayonnaise and mustard together. Spread over the top of the cauliflower. Top with cheese and return to microwave. Cook 2 to 4 minutes more or until cheese is melted.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix first seven ingredients; shape into 20 (1/2-inch) balls. Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes.
Or cook in ungreased oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch, in a 400° oven, until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain meatballs.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving. Serve with taco chips or fresh vegetables. Makes 2 cups.

title: bowl apple cake
directions: Mix in bowl the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to mixture the flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add apples and pecans. Stir.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf(for 1)
directions: Mix together
and form loaf.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet over high heat. Add flour, stirring constantly, until brown. Reduce heat; stir in shrimp. Stir constantly 3 minutes. Stir in garlic, onion, parsley and pepper for 2 minutes. Gradually add water, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thick. Stir in tomato sauce, Ro-Tel, bay leaves and salt. Bring to a boil, then lower heat to simmer; cover with lid and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with layers of dried beef (use 4 ounce jar).
Arrange pieces of chicken on beef.
Cover with slices of bacon.
Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 325°, covered.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: double date sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, water and cornstarch. Add dates and butter. Simmer 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Serve hot or warm. Can be stored in refrigerator and reheated.

title: french onion dip or vegetable dip
directions: Mix the Lipton onion soup mix to the sour cream.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar. Stir in flour and vanilla; mix well. Add pecans; set aside in refrigerator for about an hour. Divide in half. Roll in floured wax paper. Let set overnight. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix crackers, eggs and tomato sauce along with spices.
Add meat, form into loaf.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° or cook in electric skillet at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Sift sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa together into a 9-inch square baking pan.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla. Spread batter in pan.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Melt peanut butter and margarine over low heat.
Add powdered sugar.
Form into 1/2-inch balls; chill until firm.
Melt chocolate morsels in double boiler.
Add paraffin wax if too thick.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet saute onions and peppers in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives, oregano and browned ground beef.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Place half of spaghetti in a greased 13 x
9 inch baking dish.
Top with half of the vegetable mixture, sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Repeat layers. Mix soup and water until smooth; pour over casserole; sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for
30 to 35 minutes or at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through. If it starts too dry out to much add just a little hot water.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze in cupcake holders.
Garnish with strawberry and Cool Whip.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a bowl.
Make a hole in center of ingredients and add remaining ingredients. Stir just enough to dampen.
Pour mixture into 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bananas daniel
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium flame.
Add sugar and spices; stir until melted.
Place banana slices in skillet; cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add Jack Daniel's whiskey and carefully ignite.
Serve hot over ice cream.

title: monkey bread
directions: Pull apart biscuits and cut into quarters.
Dip each piece into melted butter, then roll into sugar mixture (sugars, pecans and cinnamon).
Put into greased tube pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease pan and spread in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for a sheet cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Place squash and onion in a saucepan.
Cover in water barely. Cook until tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain and mash (not too fine).
In a shallow casserole dish, mix squash mixture with eggs, butter, cheese, salt and pepper.
Top with a little more grated cheese, crushed crackers and dot with thin pieces of butter.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: snow on mountain
directions: Drain pineapple.
Place in refrigerator to jell.
Mix cottage cheese, milk, crushed pineapple and mayonnaise together.
Add to Jell-O.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add all ingredients except potatoes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add potato wedges and return to oven.
Add more wine or V-8 juice if too thick.

title: chocolate cream crunch
directions: Make crust by combining flour, pecans and margarine.
Mix well and press into bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: four winds casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and water chestnuts in oil until onion is soft.
Add tuna and parsley; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Combine soup, curry, and cream.
Stir in tuna mixture and noodles.
Reserve 1/2 cup noodles for the top.
Pour into a shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with reserved noodles.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until crisp and lightly browned.

title: the carrot cake lover's cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a greased and floured baking pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool before frosting.

title: hot mulled cider(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Tie whole spices in cheesecloth or put in tea strainer.
Cover and set on low setting for 2 to 8 hours.
Serve from crock-pot with ladle.

title: apricot delight
directions: Cook tapioca in apricot nectar with 2 cups of water added. Dissolve jello in hot water.
Combine all ingredients and pour into mold.
Chill until set or firm.
Unmold and top with whipped cream.

title: stuffed peppers 1
directions: Cut tops off peppers and wash.
Put peppers in hot water until tender.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Put hamburger back in skillet and add vegetables and rice.
Add about 1 cup of tomato sauce.
Stir well and simmer, about 15 minutes.
Place peppers in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spoon hamburger mixture into peppers until full.
Place remaining filling around peppers in dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes. Add remaining tomato sauce spooned on top of peppers and bake about 15 minutes longer.

title: lasagne with spinach(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Cook lasagne noodles as directed on package.
Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add tomato paste and sauce, mushrooms, garlic, parsley flakes, oregano, 1/2 teasapoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and water.
Simmer 1 hour.
Combine cheese, spinach, egg and rest of salt and pepper.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix crushed corn flakes and melted butter together; spread on top of potato mix.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: butter dreams(cornflake cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and baking soda gradually.
Form dough into marble size and roll in bowl of crushed cornflakes.
Flatten it a little (use bottom of a tumbler).
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, until yellow not brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: crispy-topped ravioli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place 1 can of ravioli in the bottom of a shallow casserole.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over ravioli.
Cut cheese into small squares; sprinkle half of cheese over casserole. Top with second can of ravioli, remaining cheese and corn chips. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut each fillet in 6 to 8 nuggets, about 1 1/2 inches square. Combine bread crumbs, cheese, Accent, salt and herbs.
Dip chicken nuggets in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.

title: easter's crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except crabmeat (use mixer).
Add milk to thin to a spreading consistency.
Add crabmeat.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serve in baking or chafing dish.
Great with Triscuits or ripple potato chips.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake
directions: In saucepan, mix together oleo, water and cocoa and bring to a boil.
Mix this mixture while hot with the dry ingredients.
Add vegetable shortening, buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes in an 11 x 14-inch pan.
If the pan has a lid, this cake will keep for several days without refrigeration. Spread icing while both are still hot.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Slice bread lengthwise and hollow out the center (be sure sides are not too thin).
Combine all other ingredients; mix well and spoon into bread shell.
Replace top of loaf; wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with Fritos or bread pieces from loaf's center.

title: cocktail rye tidbits
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage.
Drain very well.
Add seasoning and Velveeta cheese; simmer until cheese melts.
Put spoonfuls on cocktail rye slices; can be frozen at this point for later use. Pop under the broiler until bubbly and serve at any party.

title: four bean salad
directions: Place vegetables in large romaine-lined bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and drizzle over vegetables. Cover and marinate several hours or overnight.

title: impossible lasagne pie
directions: Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate or square 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate. Mix cooked beef, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, oregano, basil and tomato paste. Spoon evenly over top.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute by hand until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Return to oven 1 or 2 minutes until cheese melts. Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley (optional).

title: hidden hot dogs
directions: Will also need a spatula and baking pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant.
Place in cold water for 10 minutes; drain and cook in boiling water with onions and celery until tender.
Drain and mash.
Combine soup and milk, stir in eggplant. Add pepper, cheese, bread crumbs and salt.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with partially cooked bacon and bake uncovered at 350 degree for 35 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saut onions and garlic in oil; add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Brown chicken; place in a roaster which has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Pour tomato mixture over chicken and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Add vegetables; cook 1 hour or until done.
Can serve alone or over noodles.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine and beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn out of pans and cool on rack.

title: baked shrimp scampi
directions: In a small saucepan over low heat, combine butter, mustard, lemon juice, garlic and parsley.
Stir and saute about 10 minutes. Arrange shrimp in a shallow baking dish.
Pour butter mixture over shrimp.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes (shrimp will lose translucent look).
Garnish with fresh parsley and lemon wedges.

title: easy chocolate trifle
directions: Bake brownies in a 9 x 13 inch pan according to directions. Set aside. Combine milk and pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. Gently stir in 1 tub of the whipped topping. Place 1/2 of the brownie, cubed, in large serving bowl. Top with layers of 1/2 of pudding mixture, raspberries and whipped topping. Repeat layers. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: stack-a-roll stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add mushrooms with juice and mushroom soup; heat until bubbly.
Add 1/2 sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add 1/2 onion rings.
Blend and place in a casserole, about 8 x 8-inch.

title: double chocolate cookie bars
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.

title: microwave peanut clusters
directions: Melt candy chips in microwave.
Mix well.
Add peanuts.
Stir and drop on wax paper.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Place margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High until butter is melted.
Stir in flour to make a smooth paste. Add chicken broth and milk, beating with wire whip.
Microwave 6 to 7 minutes on 8 or until thick, stirring after 4 minutes and again when thick.

title: carrot fritters
directions: Scrape carrots, boil and mash.
Combine all other ingredients with carrots.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil (as with hush puppies).

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: candy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease pizza pan.
Beat together the first 8 ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes.
Pour chips and peanut butter over top while hot.
When soft, spread out over "crust." Decorate with candy.
Press in lightly.
Let cool.
Enjoy!

title: cottage cheese treat
directions: Mix cottage cheese and fruit.
Spread on toast or bread. Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: pineapple-lemon-orange punch
directions: Mix and freeze in a 2-quart container.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage around stem end with knife.
Put stem end down into a kettle.
Cover with boiling water.
Add salt and boil, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Remove; drain.
Let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix margarine, brown sugar, eggs, and bananas together.
Add dry ingredients, then walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: french silk pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter for 4 minutes or until light. Add unsweetened chocolate and vanilla. Add eggs one at a time beating on medium speed for 2 minutes after each egg, scraping bowl constantly. Turn filling into pie shell. Top with whipped cream, then curls or sprinkles if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese puffs
directions: Cook macaroni, drain, combine milk, cheese, and 1/4 tsp. salt. Over low heat till cheese melts stir small amount of hot mix into egg yolks.
Stir macaroni into crumbs pimento and onion.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar till stiff fold macaroni into all others.
Bake 325.

title: bambinas
directions: Spread Melba rounds or crackers with catsup; sprinkle cheese over catsup.
Top with pepperoni or sausage.
Sprinkle with oregano leaves, if desired.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 dozen Bambinos.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cube (don't use the skin).
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Put in flat pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut into 4-inch squares.
This makes a great luncheon casserole.
Will freeze well until baked.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: bacon cream cheese dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and knead.
Pinch off pieces and roll in hand to size of small walnut.
Bake at 300° about 30 minutes.

title: low-fat healthy bran muffins*
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dry ingredients first, then add others.
Bake for 15 minutes in greased muffin pan.
Makes 1 dozen.
There are 100 calories per muffin.

title: macaroni-fruit salad
directions: Cook rosamarina macaroni for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add mandarin oranges (juice and all), Cool Whip, pistachio pudding and pineapple.
Mix well and chill until firm.

title: peach dream delight
directions: Beat with mixer until fluffy the butter, 1 of the eggs and 1 3/4 cups powdered sugar.
Add the other egg; beat again.
Spread this mixture over half of crumbs in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Over this, put peeled, thinly sliced peaches.
Whip cream with 2 tablespoons powdered sugar; cover the peaches.
Spread the other 1/2 of the crumbs over top.
Chill overnight.
Good even after 24 hours.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil cloves, cinnamon, sugar and 2 cups of water slowly until syrupy, about 30 minutes.
Put 6 tea bags into 6 cups of boiling water.
Let stand until strong.
Remove bags.
Add strained spice mixture, juice of lemons, juice of oranges and pineapple juice. Serve hot.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cheese and bacon pancakes
directions: Saute bacon and onions in butter.
Remove from skillet. Beat egg,
milk	and
vinegar
together.
Sift
together
dry ingredients.
Gradually add milk
and
egg	mixture
to make a smooth batter.
Stir in bacon, onions and grated cheese.
Drop tablespoons of batter in well-greased pan.	Cook until bubbles rise to surface and turn.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve hot and well buttered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 400° for 60 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate drops
directions: In a large microwavable bowl, heat the chocolate chips and peanut butter together for 1 minute on High. (Some microwaves may take a little longer.)
Stir in the marshmallows.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet or wax paper and chill in the refrigerator until firm.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Mix sugar, turmeric, mustard seed and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Put in sterile jars and seal.

title: creamed peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook peas in boiling salted water until tender.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until lightly browned.
Add to peas. Stir flour into remaining drippings, adding more butter if needed.
Add half and half gradually, cooking and stirring until slightly thickened.
Turn heat to low.
Add sliced cheese; stir until dissolved.
Pour sauce over peas; heat until bubbly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay crescent rolls out flat on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes; cool.
Mix the other ingredients, then spread on cool rolls.
Top with small chopped or shredded vegetables, such as broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, radishes, etc.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Make cake according to package instructions.
Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water, then add pop.
Poke holes in cake while hot and pour Jell-O mixture over cake.
Cool.
Mix pudding according to package instructions, then add Cool Whip.
Pour over cake and cool for approximately 1 hour.

title: whole wheat bubble bread
directions: Grease 2-quart deep casserole dish or 2 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup
and level off.
In large bowl, combine bread flour, sugar, salt and dry yeast.
Blend well.
In small saucepan, heat milk and margarine until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add egg and blend into flour mixture.
Beat at low speed until mixed and moistened with mixer blades.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in whole wheat flour to form stiff dough.
On floured surface, knead in 1 to 1 1/2 cups additional bread flour until dough is smooth and elastic (5 to 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel.

title: souffle baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool completely.
Cut in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving 1/8-inch thick shells.
Combine potato pulp, milk, sour cream, chives, salt and pepper in a bowl; mash with a potato masher until smooth.
Set aside.

title: seafoam frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, brown sugar, salt and water in double boiler; beat over boiling water for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat 1 more minute.
Frost cake immediately.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix in glass bowl Karo, peanuts and sugar; microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Stir and microwave for 4 more minutes.
Stir in margarine and baking soda.
Quickly spread thin on slightly buttered foil.
Cool.
Break apart.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: turkey loaf italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a loaf pan with olive oil Pam. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour mixture into prepared loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
(Onion soup mix may be used instead of tomato soup mix but increase the ketchup to 1 1/2 cups.)

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add oats and coconut.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, cream and peanut butter with mixer.
Fold in 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip and freeze.

title: lasagne
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch dish with spirals, then layer with slices of Swiss cheese; layer with cottage cheese and then spaghetti sauce. Lay strips of Mozzarella cheese on top and heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pumpkin, water and oil and mix again.
Then add dry ingredients and mix.
For baking, use 4 one pound round coffee cans or 2 loaf pans.
Do not grease cans. Pour mixture into cans.
Fill to half way mark.

title: south of the border (dip)(oh so easy, oh so good!)
directions: Place (mound) raw sausage in cleaned mushroom cavities; bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until sausage is thoroughly cooked.
Be sure to place mushrooms on drip pan so some of the fat can drip away.

title: spinach cottage cheese casserole
directions: Spinach may also be steamed or cooked in the microwave. Combine
spinach,
eggs
and cottage cheese; place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Do not prepare ahead of time unless you cook it; eggs will separate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This
is	a
wonderful
dish to take to a covered dish supper.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sweet potato and jalapeno pepper soup
directions: Melt butter and cook onion about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and sweet potatoes.
If using fresh potatoes, simmer until soft. If using canned potatoes, heat for 5 minutes.
When potatoes are tender, strain soup.
Place solids in blender with a little liquid and puree.
Add mixture back to liquid and add jalapeno pepper, corn kernels, salt and pepper.
Serve in soup bowls with sour cream on top.

title: chess cake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix cake mix, 1 egg and butter together.
Press into rectangular cake pan.
Press cup of chopped nuts into batter.
Mix together sugar, 2 eggs, cream cheese and vanilla and pour over the batter and nuts.
Cook 1 hour.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add milk and oil all at once to flour mixture.
Stir with fork just enough for dough to hold together.
Pat dough about 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut out biscuits with floured 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 9 biscuits.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Put crackers on a baking sheet. Top with 1/3 slice bacon. Sprinkle with sugar; bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Mix crumbs and pack 2/3 in a 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: muffin toppers
directions: Thoroughly blend butter and mustard; spread on muffin halves. Divide ham between muffins.
Top with cheese.
Place on micro-proof plate and cook on 55 (Defrost) for 2 minutes.
Let stand 1 minute before serving.

title: tomato flitter
directions: In a frying pan, let oil set on stove eye until you mix the flour and water, then fry until golden brown.
Put in plate and cut in half.
On one half, put mayonnaise and on the other half put your tomatoes.
Salt it and put it together.
Eat and enjoy!

title: pyracantha jelly
directions: Boil berries and water in kettle 20 minutes.
Add juices and drain mixture through jelly bag.
Do not squeeze.
This should be sufficient to make 4 to 4 1/2 cups juice.
Add powdered pectin according to directions on package and then add sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans; put in crock-pot with all other ingredients.
Add enough water to cook beans.
Cook on low heat all day.
When ready to serve, remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot cooked rice with buttered French bread and a tossed salad.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate until needed.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Toss blueberries lightly with 2 tablespoons sugar; set aside. Mix remaining dry ingredients in bowl; make well in center. Combine egg, milk, and oil. Add all at once to dry ingredients. Stir quickly only till dry ingredients are moistened. Gently stir in blueberries. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full. Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: chicken or turkey a la king
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir mushrooms and green pepper in butter 5 minutes.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream, broth and reserved mushroom liquid.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute or so.
Stir in chicken; heat through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pistachio delight
directions: Slice cake and place on bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and pour over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo, adding sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg yolks.
Sift flour with baking powder and spices.
Add to the first mixture a little flour and milk, until all is used.
Beat the batter hard; add spices.
Mix the chocolate with the hot mashed potatoes.
Add the whites of 2 eggs, beaten stiff.
Add chocolate and nuts to the cake batter and bake in three layers in a moderate oven.

title: dressing
directions: Mash up the corn bread first, then put in the eggs, the celery, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper and sage, then mix, then put in the milk, butter, broth and chicken.
Put in oven and bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Take peanut butter and icing and put on low on the stove.
Let it melt together.
Put it in a dish.

title: lime mint tea
directions: Boil sugar and water; cool.
Pour tea over mint leaves; cool and strain.
Combine lemon and lime juices with cooled sugar mixture.
Serve in chilled tall glasses, filled with crushed ice. Top each glass with a lime slice.
Garnish with a sprig of mint. Yields 18 to 20 glasses.

title: apple crisp
directions: Line buttered dish with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and granulated sugar.
Mix together flour, brown sugar and butter.
Add water to slices apples, then cover with mixture.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then turn down to 350° and finish baking.

title: white bread plus
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup warm water.
Let sit 5 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Stir until thick.
Add sour cream, then Cool Whip.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of sliced bananas, then a layer of pudding.
Repeat and have pudding mixture on top.
Crumble up some wafers and sprinkle on top.
Can use strawberries, cherries, peaches or pineapple instead of bananas as every layer.
Try one of these for an extra good taste.
(I use pineapple.)

title: good-to-the-last-lick casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
In buttered 2-quart baking dish, layer as follows:
potatoes (sprinkle with salt and pepper), 2 tablespoons flour, cream-style corn, salt, pepper, 1 tablespoon flour, beef, onions and tomato soup.
Spread evenly over beef to sides of casserole dish.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 50 minutes, then uncover and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: In top of boiler, over boiling water, melt marshmallows with milk. Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Place marshmallows in larger bowl.
Fold in chocolate mixture. Drop teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill 2 hours until firm.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vinegar and pie shells.
Add the vinegar to the mixture.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes, or until brown.

title: christmas soup
directions: Put the first 10 items in a pot and cover; simmer until vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend milk and flour together well.
Pour into mixture and cook until thickened.
Stir in cheese until it melts good.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together.
Beat egg well; add milk.
Stir in oil and lemon juice.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir about 20 seconds.
When just a few patches of flour are left, fold in blueberries, gently.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for about 25 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with grapes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove skin from breasts and halve then coat the pieces with the crumbs mixed with salt, pepper and tarragon.
Brown the chicken on all sides in 4 tablespoons of the butter in a skillet.
Place the pieces in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Add the onion to the butter left in the skillet and cook until tender.
Pour in the stock and wine and bring to a boil.
Pour around the chicken.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Saute the mushrooms in the remaining butter and add along with the grapes to the chicken.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes longer.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon cream cheese squares
directions: Unroll one tube of crescent rolls and place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Seal seams, set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread over dough.
Unroll second tube and place over cream cheese mixture, seal seams.
May have to stretch to fit.
Brush butter over top evenly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and rest of sugar.
May use more sugar if needed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix salmon, eggs, crumbs, onion and seasonings.
Form into patties and fry until brown.
Make sauce by melting butter.
Add flour to make paste.
Add milk to make a white sauce.
Season and add peas last.
Cover fried patties with sauce.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook onion in butter in a saucepan over medium heat until transparent.
Add the beef and cook, stirring, until beef is light brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper, mushrooms and soup.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add the sour cream and simmer for 15 minutes longer. Serve over rice and garnish with paprika.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs, add oil and beat.
Add flour and baking powder, mix apples and cinnamon last.
Bake at 350° in a rectangular pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Set aside.
Saute onions and add to remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then simmer.
Crumble bacon over chowder before serving.

title: tomato salad with basil-buttermilk dressing
directions: Blend 2 cups fresh basil, buttermilk, sliced green onions and salt in processor until smooth.
Transfer to bowl.
Add mayonnaise and pepper. Whisk until dressing is smooth. Let stand 30 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(Can be made 8 hours ahead. Cover tightly and refrigerate.)

title: un-fried french fries
directions: You will also need light vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: chocolate cheesecake pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, sugar, cocoa and margarine; press firmly on bottom and up sides to rim of 9-inch pie plate.
In mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk then melted chocolate chips.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mary bowden's fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit well except the pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: spanish paella
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large paella pan or iron skillet, saute onion and red bell pepper in butter until softened.
Add rice to pan and cook 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add more butter, if necessary.
Stir in chicken broth and saffron and bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce to a low simmer and cook, uncovered, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, then beat eggs and mix well with other ingredients.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sherry's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Bake, in a greased loaf pan, at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl.
Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice, ending with pudding.
(I crush wafers and sprinkle on top.)
Cover and chill.

title: kate's date pudding("will keep for months and may be reheated".)
directions: Those were the entire original directions.
More complete directions: Crisco instead of lard and measure flour about 5 1/2 to 6 cups.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add molasses. Mix cinnamon and ginger into 2 cups flour and add.
(Note:
Place vinegar in measuring cup and hold over mixing bowl while adding the baking soda; beat into mixture with remaining flour.)

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Brown the chicken.
Saute the other ingredients and place chicken in mixture.
Add 5 to 6 cups of water.
For best results, allow to stand overnight in refrigerator.
The day you serve it, bring mixture to a hard boil.
Add the rice.
When rice starts to surface, turn off the heat and cover.
If it dries up too much, add hot water.
It should be moist or soupy, one-half hour. Garnish with parsley and pimentos.
It goes well with just a salad.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Place a slice of ham portrait-style on counter.
Take a paper towel and wipe off moisture.
Spread cream cheese on ham.
Cut off the root of a green onion; place green onion along bottom edge of ham and roll into a pinwheel.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices with a sharp knife.
Refrigerate.

title: neapolitan chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in cooker.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Good with hot garlic bread. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook capellini, rinse and drain.
Add vegetables.
Add 3/4 (12 ounce) Italian dressing.
Pour over Salad Supreme.
Mix. Cover and leave overnight before serving.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Dice apples, add sugar and let stand for 1 hour.
Add oil and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Bake in a 350° oven in 8-inch square pan for about 45 minutes.

title: chinese-style vegetables
directions: In medium skillet, mix water and vegetables.
Cover; steam until crisp-tender (about 5 minutes).
Stir several times.
Season with salt and pepper; stir in soy sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, scallions, egg, bread crumbs, 1 tablespoon soy sauce and 1 teaspoon minced ginger.
Shape into 24 balls.
In large skillet, heat 1 tablespoon oil over medium-high heat.
Add meatballs; cook until browned, about 12 minutes. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Wipe skillet clean.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, wine, cornstarch, sugar and 2 tablespoons water in a small bowl; set aside.
In skillet, heat remaining 1 tablespoon oil over medium heat.
Add garlic; cook 1 minute.
Add remaining 1 teaspoon ginger; cook 1 minute.
Add vegetables and soy sauce mixture.
Bring to a simmer; cook 1 minute.
Return meatballs to pan.
Cover and cook until heated through, 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.
Per serving:
376 cals.; 27 g. protein; 23 g. fat; 128 mg. chol.; 17 g.
carbs.; 927 mg. sodium.
Work time:
35 minutes; ready to serve in 35 minutes.

title: oven omelette
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in pan.
Mix everything together.
Bake 35 minutes or until set (when knife inserted comes out clean).

title: banana peach delight
directions: Combine water and Jell-O.
Cook until dissolved.
Put remaining ingredients into blender.
Divide into 1/2-cup servings.
Can be frozen.

title: bubble pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce. Quarter the biscuits; place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: aunt margaret's hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in large container thoroughly.
Place 1 or 2 heaping teaspoons in boiling water for 1 cup of hot chocolate.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Combine the next 4 ingredients. Add vegetables.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Rice Krispies, mixed with the melted butter.
Bake in a 350°oven for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: jellied pig's feet(koseliena)
directions: Wash meat; put into a large pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boiling point and skim.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer slowly, about 3 to 4 hours until meat is done and comes off the bones.
Cool, strain, remove bones and spices.
Return meat to liquid; add pepper, 1/2 clove of garlic, minced and more salt if desired to suit your taste.
Pour into loaf pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Scrape fat from the top before serving.

title: hearty tortellini soup
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, cook garlic in margarine for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini with the precooked meatballs and heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes more. Serve topped with cheese.
*Be careful not to burn garlic.

title: black bottom cups
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add the water, oil, vinegar and vanilla to sifted ingredients; beat until combined.
Fill paper muffin cups 1/3 full.
Top with 1 teaspoon of the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 24.

title: herb bread sticks
directions: With oleo at room temp., blend in basil leaves, garlic and thyme.
Cut buns into sticks, butter and bake at 300° until brown and crispy.

title: soft granola bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix brown sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl with spoon until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients except Honey Glaze. Spread in pan with spatula, patting evenly with hand.
Bake just until center is set but not firm, 17 to 22 minutes; cool 15 minutes.
Drizzle evenly with Honey Glaze; cool completely.
Cut into bars, about 3 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 40 bars.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain.
Add flour and soup.
Add enough water to make easy to simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over buns.

title: cran-raspberry ring
directions: Dissolve raspberry and lemon gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen raspberries, breaking up large pieces.
Add cranberry-orange relish.
Chill until cold but not set.
Carefully pour in lemon-lime beverage.
Stir gently.
Chill until partially set. Turn into 6 to 6 1/2-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp greens.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stick-on treats
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine and heat on low or microwave 4 cups marshmallows, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Add remaining marshmallows and corn and rice cereals.
Stir to coat pieces evenly.
Spread cereal mixture into prepared pan with back of buttered spoon.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place a layer of sliced, boiled potatoes in a well-buttered casserole pan and cover with pieces of ham.

Then add a little sour cream, then a layer of sliced, hard-boiled eggs and more sour cream, then a layer of cooked cauliflower and more sour cream. Add the top layer of sliced potatoes and sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: dijon chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix first four ingredients.
Dip chicken in mixture, then in bread crumbs to coat.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bring remaining dip mixture to a boil.
Stir until smooth.
Serve as sauce. Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple jiffy cake
directions: Note:
Be sure to use Jiffy cake mix, since a regular cake mix is too much cake and will not turn out as well.

title: banana pineapple dessert
directions: *Sugar-free reduced calorie Jell-O pudding is okay (and good).

title: vinegar pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar. Add the rest of the ingredients and place in a saucepan. Cook until thick.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil macaroni; follow directions on package.
Drain and rinse well.
Set macaroni aside.
When cool, mix macaroni with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Set inside refrigerator until chilled.
Serve.

title: grandma ruth's stuffing
directions: Put parsley, onions and celery into blender with a little water.
Chop, not all at once, or use a food processor.
Soak rolls. Squeeze out water and break up well with hands.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix well and pour into a Pyrex dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: steak tartare
directions: Make a paste of mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce. Chop 1/2 can of the anchovies.
Mix paste, anchovies and all other ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into loaf on a platter and place remaining anchovy fillets on top.
Decorate with lots of parsley.
Serve with lots of buttered bread.
Serves 4.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter.
Add barbecue sauce, pepper, garlic and chopped green onions.
Bring to boil; remove from heat and let cool for 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil again.
Test shrimp to be sure they are cooked.

title: pineapple au gratin casserole
directions: Combine pineapple, reserved juice and cheese.
Mix flour and sugar and stir into pineapple.
Pour into a greased casserole dish. Cover with crushed ritz crackers.
Melt butter and drizzle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: You will need 18 cupcake papers.

title: dried apple pies
directions: Place apples in water and cook them almost dry.
Add 2 cups sugar into the cooked apples and cook them as dry as you can without burning them.
Add tsp. vanilla flavoring and mix well. Take one biscuit out of pack and roll out flat; biscuit must be rolled to the size of a big crisco can lid.
Place 1 tablespoon of cooked apples on one side of rolled out dough; fold the other side of the dough over the top of apples and press edges together with a fork.
Place apple pies in cooking oil in saucepan and cook to golden brown on both sides.

title: mints
directions: Knead sugar and cream cheese. Add just a dab of food coloring, not too much.
Add flavoring.
Coat inside of mold with sugar. Press dough into mold.
Press out.
Makes 75 to 100 mints.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onions. Drain. Add chili powder, tomato paste, and beans. Melt velveeta, Ro-tel, and chicken soup together. Spray bottom of 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Put meat mixture in large flour tortilla shell and roll up.
Place tortillas in pan. Pour cheese mixture over tortillas. Bake for 30 - 45 minutes at 350. Makes 10 - 12 large enchiladas.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put thin layer of cracker crumbs in buttered dish.
Cover with asparagus.
Then pour soup mixture over this.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat oven to 375°.
Put casserole in oven and turn oven to 300°; bake 20 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ground beef in skillet- cook until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients- stir well.
Put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour (or until potatoes are done) at 325 degrees.

title: peach delight
directions: Spray bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish sprayed with Pam. Mix ingredients and press in bottom of prepared dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until brown.
Set aside to cool.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Put pork chops in a pan with sides or ovenproof dish.
Pour dressing over chops.
Let set about 1 hour, turning several times. Cover with foil and cook on 350° until done.
Great grilled!

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Add creamed mixture to dry ingredients.
Add chocolate morsels and pecans; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork(microwave main dish)
directions: Place carrots and oil in 3-quart microwave casserole; stir to coat.
Cover and place in oven (cook on High 4 minutes).
Add pork green pepper and onion.
Mix lightly.
Cover.
(Cook on High 5 minutes.)
Dissolve cornstarch in reserved pineapple juice. Stir in remaining ingredients except pineapple.
Cover; cook (50) for 15 minutes.
Stir; cover and cook (50) for 15 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.
Sprinkle with chow mein noodles.

title: icebox oatmeal cookies
directions: Form into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight. Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers well.
Add box of sugar and pecans.
Mix well.
Add oleo and orange juice.
Mix well and make into balls. Roll in coconut.
These can be made early and frozen.
Good for Christmas.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Unroll dough and place on greased 10 x 13-inch baking pan. Press edges to seal. Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix in bowl; mix well.
Spread on crust and top with chopped vegetables and shredded cheese.
Cut into bars. Substitute fresh vegetables of your choice.
Sometimes called vegetable pizza.

title: sugar free apple pieroswell, new mexico
directions: Soak Tapioca in thawed apple juice.
Prepare apples and crust. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples and add juice.

title: quick cajun seafood bisque
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat (medium) and serve.
Makes 10 servings. This can be heated in a crock-pot (low) or rice cooker.

title: oyster crax snack
directions: Mix all ingredients but crackers.
Pour over crackers and stir until coated.
Heat in microwave on High for 2 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Put crumbs of cornbread and white bread in big pot.
Add celery, bell pepper, onions and poultry seasoning mix.
Add broth and eggs; mix.
You want it like pancake mix.
Put in pan and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until browned.

title: potpourri
directions: Mix together in airtight jar.
Give a shake every now and then.
Add whole cloves or cinnamon.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion and beef together until hot, but not browned.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Cut fish into serving pieces.
Add salt and seafood seasoning to water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Add frozen fish and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with melted butter.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all, except biscuits, and place into buttered baking dish. Place biscuits on top and bake at 400° until biscuits are done. Brush biscuits with butter and serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: fried rice and beef
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients in oil.
Add all other ingredients and fry.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add salt, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Beat well.
Add eggs, beating after each one.
Stir in flour.
Cook in 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Combine melted butter, sugar, milk and flour together, mixing well.
Pour into a deep baking dish.
In a small bowl, put blueberries, sugar and spice to taste.
Stir well.
Pour blueberries over batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Pour juice over the berries.

title: delicious vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 2 hours.
Add last 4 ingredients for the last hour.
Stir more frequently after you add the corn and sugar.
(They can cause the soup to stick.)
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain well.
Combine soup and sour cream; stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and onion.
Combine stuffing and butter.
Spread 1/2 stuffing in 12-inch casserole.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top; sprinkle remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, salt, vinegar and spices.
Pour over cucumbers and onions and refrigerate.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Cut up chicken as for frying.
Mix all ingredients for sauce together; bring to boil.
Dip pieces of chicken in hot sauce and place in casserole which has tight fitting cover.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Place covered casserole in a 350° oven.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, spooning sauce over the chicken occasionally.

title: easy cajun baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts into melted butter.
Sprinkle Cajun seasoning liberally on both sides.
Broil (high heat) for 7 to 8 minutes, then turn chicken and broil another 7 minutes.
Serve hot with rice and bread.

title: easy spanish main dish
directions: Prepare Spanish rice as directed on package.
Brown ground meat with chopped onion and pepper.
Add to cooked Spanish rice and simmer about 10 minutes more.
Delicious!

title: biscuit mix
directions: Mix flour, soda and lard.
Cover and store in the refrigerator. Keeps for 1 month.
Makes 10 cups.
When needed, mix a batch with 1/2 cup milk and 2 cups mix and bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook and stir sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt in a saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Without stirring, continue cooking until syrup forms a brittle ball when a drop is tested in cold water.
Add small quantity of vanilla, stirring only enough to mix it through the hot syrup.
Pour hot syrup over popped corn and mix. Moisten hands and, with quick action, shape to desired form. (Color syrup with cake coloring if desired.)

title: megan's pink stuff
directions: Mix Jell-O, pineapple, Cool Whip and cottage cheese well.
Add pecans. For a large amount, double ingredients.
For variety, use your favorite Jell-O.

title: homemade noodles for soup
directions: Add yellow food coloring if desired.

title: bacon and cheese potatoes
directions: Skin, dice and boil potatoes. Fry bacon crisp and then crumble.
Dice onion. Shred cheese and set aside 1/4 cup of the cheese.
In an 11 x 14-inch dish, mix all ingredients except 1/4 cup of the cheese. Salt and pepper to taste.
Press down in pan and then add remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: company french toast
directions: Melt in saucepan the brown sugar, margarine and cinnamon. Layer bread slices and pancake syrup in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix eggs and sugar and pour over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stephen's spaghetti
directions: Boil noodles in boiling water until tender.
Heat Prego meat sauce until steaming.
Butter and put garlic salt on French bread and brown in oven.
Put noodles on plate and top with Prego. Drink new Coke.

title: banana bread(club member: jason baldwin)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sift flour, baking soda and salt.

Cream together sugar and butter with a wooden spoon. Break bananas into small chunks; add to sugar and butter. Add eggs and beat well. Mix to a batter consistency and pour into a buttered loaf pan. Bake 1 hour.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread.
Set for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a pan of water. Cover until almost done.
(Can add a little onion.)

title: venison pileau
directions: * Kitchen Bouqet or instant coffee to darken rice if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Lay uncooked noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place a layer of sauce, sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.
(Alternate sour cream and cottage cheese.)
Make 3 layers.
In my middle layer, I sometimes add olives. Top it with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Pour tomato sauce and water over the layers.
Cover tightly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking dish. Bake until golden brown on top, approximately 30 minutes. Serve with crackers or bagel chips.

title: hot dog slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients; serve over hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: 9 day slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, salad oil, salt and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage while hot.
Put in covered glass container and keep refrigerated.

title: yogurt chicken
directions: Skin all chicken pieces.
Divide each leg into 2 pieces (drumstick and thigh).
Quarter the chicken breast.
Pat dry the chicken pieces and set aside.
Put 1/2 cup yogurt in a bowl.
Add 3/4 cup water, a little at a time, beating with a fork as you do so.
Peel all the onions.
Cut 4 in half, lengthwise, then slice them into half-rings, about 1/8-inch thick.
Chop the other onion coarsely.
Put the chopped onion, garlic and ginger in an electric blender.
Add 6 tablespoons of water and blend to a smooth paste. Heat 5 tablespoons of oil in a 10-inch pot over medium heat.
Put in the sliced onions, frying for 8 to 10 minutes until dark brown but still limp.
Set aside.
Add remaining oil to pot.
Fry chicken until browned on all sides.
Turn heat to low and pour paste into the pot.

title: overnight buns
directions: Start about 5 p.m.
Dissolve sugar in warm water.
When cool, add yeast and stir.
Add salt and beaten egg, then 5 cups flour and beat well.
Next add shortening and knead in other 5 cups of water.
Cover pan with foil and put in warm place.
Knead down every hour.
Put in pans at 10 p.m.
Cover with cloth and plastic. Bake the next morning at 8 a.m. at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: freezing blueberries
directions: Do not wash fresh berries until ready to use.
Freeze berries without washing.
Unwashed berries will freeze individually and can be easily poured from containers in desired amount.
Rinse frozen berries in cold water just before using.

title: flora's rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour over Crisco, butter, salt and sugar. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast to butter and Crisco mixture.
Add eggs.
Last, stir in flour.
Keep in refrigerator. Take out what you want each time.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.
Put in airtight bowl.

title: cocoa light cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add Crisco and 3/4 cup milk and beat for 2 minutes, then add baking powder.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup milk, vanilla and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes and bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: great tuna salad
directions: Chop apple and pour enough lemon juice over to prevent apple from turning dark.
Add all other ingredients and mix.

title: "jello salad"
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add box dry pudding.
Drain fruits and add other items.

title: apple walnut upside-down cake
directions: In a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, melt butter.
Add a half cup brown sugar and blend.
Peel and core apples.
From each apple, slice 3 medium thick rings (9 total).
Chop the remaining apples and reserve about a cup.
Place the apple rings on top of the brown sugar.
Put a cherry in the center of each.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the egg, beat well.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt.
Combine the molasses and water, add alternately with the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Fold in the reserved chopped apple and black walnuts. Bake in a preheated moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes or until well done.
Let stand on cake rack for 5 minutes.
Invert over serving plate and remove pan.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. In heavy saucepan, cook caramels and milk over low heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted.
Keep warm.

title: no bake hi-protein quickie cookies
directions: Mix dates with 1/2 cup flour.
In cup, dissolve gelatine in water and set aside.
In a large bowl, combine oats, coconut, wheat germ, nuts and dates.
In saucepan mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add oleo and bring to a boil (just until butter melts).
Add vanilla and maple flavoring.
Add softened gelatin.
Stir and cook about 1 minute.

title: crisco rolls
directions: Pour
hot water over Crisco, sugar and salt.
Blend and let cool.
Beat
eggs.	Put
yeast
in warm water;
dissolve. Add yeast
and	eggs
to cooled Crisco mixture and blend.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover and set in refrigerator 4 hours (or overnight).

title: wood stove potpourri
directions: Mix well and add 2 to 3 tablespoons per pint of water.
Simmer on stove.

title: easy and elegant camp stew
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 quarts.
You can freeze it.
Great reheated.

title: cucumber-cream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding salt, pepper and vinegar to get the desired taste.
Chill before using or set on a bed of ice for a summer buffet outside.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add the cranberry sauce and oranges; mix well.
Pour into mold; chill until almost set (about 1 1/2 hours).
Dissolve lemon juice in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
In a blender, combine the cream cheese, nuts and lemon jello.
Blend until smooth.
Add the pineapple into the lemon jello mix and pour this into the jello mold.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and rub with oil.
Bake at 400° until done.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp; stir in butter and 1 1/2 cups of cheese; add rest of ingredients.
Stuff shells with potato mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon cheese pie
directions: Combine lemon jello and hot water; set aside to cool.
Mix together well the cream cheese, vanilla (or lemon flavoring), lemon juice and sugar.
Beat chilled evaporated milk until real thick.
Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: mints
directions: Put butter and milk in 2-quart microproof bowl.
Cook on High for 45 seconds, or until butter is melted.
Stir in frosting mix. Cook on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until bubbly.
Stir twice during cooking time.
Stir in food coloring to tint.
Add extract. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Cook package of rice.
Add all ingredients in a casserole and heat in a 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Serve with cole slaw, baked apples or fruit salad and rolls.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into loaf.

title: elegant party cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package and bake in an 11 1/2 x 18 x 1-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° until done, 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert on racks or foil-covered cardboard.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and sour cream, add 1/4 taco seasoning.
Beat until smooth, spread on pizza pan.
Brown ground chuck, drain and add rest of seasoning and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool, put on top of cheese, add lettuce, then tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, (you can add green peppers and sliced ripe olives, if wanted).
Dip tortilla chips.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream and water in a saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Add nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto buttered sheets or waxed paper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in bottom of pie shell.
Combine the water, sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Continue cooking over low heat 2 more minutes.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Pour cooked mixture over berries.
Chill until set. Serve with whipped cream.

title: barb's irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put flour, white sugar, soda and salt in a large bowl.
Chop cold butter into small pieces and put in the bowl of dry ingredients.
Using a pastry cutter, work ingredients into a crumbly mixture.
Add the orange zest and currants and mix until thoroughly covered.
Add buttermilk, mixing until you get a wet dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured board. Knead until a ball forms.
Turn onto an ungreased cookie sheet, forming a loaf almost 7 inches across; flatten slightly.
Sprinkle granulated sugar on top liberally.
Cut halfway through into 4 sections.
Bake in a preheated oven at 425° on a low rack for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cover with a cloth.
Cut into 4 sections and slice.
Freezes well.
