title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Combine all vegetables in a bowl and mix well.
Stir in softened cream cheese and add enough mayonnaise to make of spreading consistency.
Stir in salt to taste.
If desired, add a little horseradish.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Drain out spices; top with orange slices.
Enjoy!

title: fish and chips
directions: Fold enough fish pieces into batter bowl at once for one frying.
Deep fry in Crisco at 375° to 400°.
Serve with lemon or tartar sauce.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese on stove top in saucepan; stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn chips, Tostitos or any kind of dip.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt. Stir in next 3 ingredients. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to boiling. Cook 2 minutes. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to
hot mixture, stirring constantly. Cook and stir 2 minutes. Cool to room temperature; spoon into cooled pastry shell.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Skin chicken.
Saute on grill until light brown and fully cooked.
Place on large pan.
In frying pan, take wine, tarragon and chicken base; bring to a boil.
Add heavy cream and sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: ole-but goodie spoon bread
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Slowly add meal and salt to boiling water and cook.
Stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add butter.
Beat well.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: taco stew
directions: In a big pot, brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Dump in all ingredients and simmer for an hour or so.
Serve with cornbread or hot tortillas.

title: spiced pears
directions: Mix sugar, water, vinegar and cloves.
Bring to boil.
Add washed pears that have skins on.
Push cloves into pears, if desired.
Cook pears until tender.
Place in cans and seal.

title: moon cake
directions: Mix water and margarine together.
Bring to a boil. Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool a little while.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating well with spoon or mixer.
Spread on ungreased cookie sheet, 11 x 15-inches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
(It will look like the moon's surface, all lumpy and bumpy, that's why it's called Moon Cake!)
Don't prick, leave cake as is.

title: shrimp and spaghetti au gratin
directions: Arrange shrimp in large shallow pan.
Combine herbs, spices and seasonings.
Sprinkle over the shrimp.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and butter.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs and pickles.
Also salad dressing.
Moisten with salad dressing and serve on lettuce. Garnish with additional egg slices and olives.

title: tasty mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender; drain.
Mash with electric mixer.

title: quick spanish beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, green pepper and rice to vegetable oil in large skillet.
Stir over high heat until lightly browned.
Add ground beef, tomato sauce and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Bring quickly to a boil.
Cover tightly and simmer until rice is tender.

title: 2 way cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat; add oatmeal mixture and stir.
Add other ingredients and mix well with your hands.
It will be stiff.
Put a bowl of water on table and use it to wet your hands before you shape cookies.
Roll cookies into small balls or other shapes.
Put cookies on lightly buttered cookie sheet; flatten and bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven or eat cookies right away.

title: roy's favorite cookies
directions: Combine crushed vanilla wafers, sugar, nuts, cocoa, honey and bourbon or rum in medium size bowl and mix well.
Mixture should be moist but not soggy.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well and bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter in pan in which bars are to be baked.
Spread graham crackers over butter evenly.
Sprinkle on chocolate and butterscotch morsels, coconut and nuts.
Pour sweetened condensed milk over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into bars when cool.

title: good chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces (I like breast meat) in baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake about one hour or less.
Good over cooked rice.

title: fig strawberry preserves
directions: Thoroughly mix figs, jello and sugar in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat and continue boiling for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour quickly into prepared jars and seal.
Makes 6 jars.

title: wendy's frosty
directions: In a blender, mix on high speed the milk, chocolate and ice cream.
Serve cold.
Enjoy!

title: shaggy dogs
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, egg, dates and nuts in a saucepan and cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour over Rice Krispies and let cool until you can handle it.
Shape into finger-like rolls and roll in coconut and confectioners sugar.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Pour chilled evaporated milk into a cold bowl.
Add lemon juice and whisk until stiff.
Fold in a few grains of salt, sugar, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours. Serves 6.

title: simple yeast rolls
directions: Combine water and yeast; add and mix oil, sugar and flour. Knead dough.
Roll out and cut biscuits.
Melt butter and brush on top of biscuits.
Let set for 30 minutes.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: potatoes anna
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
With 3 tablespoons butter, grease an 8-inch skillet with heat resistant handle and tight fitting cover. Gently toss potatoes with salt and pepper.
Layer a third of potato slices, circular fashion, around bottom and side of skillet. Dot with butter.
Repeat twice.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind and melted butter. Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake in a 300° oven until knife comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes. Good pie to use up egg yolks after making divinity candy.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix lemonade and orange juice according to directions.
Add pineapple juice and sugar.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake until firm, 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Best if served warm with ice cream.

title: cheesy chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove and dice.
Boil spaghetti in the chicken broth (16 oz.).
Saute bell pepper and onion in one stick of oleo. Add this mixture to the spaghetti.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, nacho cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup, Velveeta cheese and chicken. Stir until cheese melts.
Bake in casserole dish 15 to 20 minutes at 450°.

title: aunt lucy's mud hens
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 7 ingredients together. Spread very thin in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Beat egg whites stiff and add brown sugar.
Spread over nuts and bake for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot. Yield: 24 (2-inch) squares.

title: snap-e-tom chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts to seal in juices. Combine tomato and chile cocktail from concentrate and mushroom soup (this mixture is great as a gravy). Add chicken to the liquid mix. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer until chicken is done. Serve over a bed of rice.

title: broccoli and cauliflower casserole
directions: Saute onion
in butter.
Add soup, cheese and milk.
In separate
saucepans cook broccoli and cauliflower according to package directions.
Add
to
mixture,
stir and pour into a 2 1/2-quart
casserole.
Mix
together
butter and bread crumbs, sprinkle on casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbly. Serves 10.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Place in baking dish and cover with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: easy apple muffins
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs.
Add sugar, butter and salt and work together thoroughly.
Add milk and egg and then stir in baking powder.

title: sweet sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop onions fine.
Combine with 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out liquid.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes. Drain.
Chop apples. Add cabbage, vinegar and sugar. Cover with water. Cook until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Make roux of bacon and 2 tablespoons flour (until browned).
Add 1 cup cabbage liquid. Stir until smooth.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown onion in skillet.
Add meat, salt and pepper and fry until done.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Soften the cream cheese. Add sifted powdered sugar. Add 3 beaten eggs. Cream together and pour onto crust. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: smalandsk ostkaka(cheese cake)
directions: Stir the cottage cheese by hand or with mixer until granular. Add the flour, eggs, sugar, cream and almonds.
Mix well.
Grease a 10-inch fluted pie pan or an 8-inch square baking pan.
Pour in the mixture and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Garnish with whipped cream and jelly.

title: green bean salad
directions: Drain water off vegetables.
Then add pimiento, celery, onion and green pepper.
In a saucepan bring sugar, pepper, salt, vinegar and oil to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Put all into a large bowl, mix well with a spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix with cream cheese, 1 cup chopped nuts, bell pepper, onion, pimento and salt.
Form into ball or log and roll in remaining nuts.

title: stuffed lettuce, country style
directions: Select a firm head of lettuce and remove the center leaving a good shell.
Wash and drain the lettuce.
After all the water is drained from the lettuce, chop the lettuce from the center very fine and mix with the remaining ingredients.
Pack the mixture firmly but carefully into the lettuce shell.
Wrap in waxed paper or cheesecloth and chill.
Slice and serve with French dressing.

title: boston creams
directions: Boil all ingredients together until a firm ball is formed in a cup of cold water.
Cool; beat and pour out on a greased pan or platter.

title: english toffee
directions: Combine butter and water in a 4-quart Dutch oven; cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Add sugar and salt, mixing well. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil gently until mixture begins to lighten in color.
Add 1 cup walnuts; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer registers 298°.
Pour syrup mixture into a buttered 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan, spreading to edges of pan.
Cool slightly; mark into 1-inch squares with the sharp edge of a knife.
Cool thoroughly.
Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler over boiling water.
Spread chocolate over fudge; sprinkle with remaining walnuts. Let stand until chocolate is firm.
Break into squares.
Yield:
About 3 pounds.

title: shoo fly cake
directions: Mix and let stand to cool first 3 ingredients. Keep 3/4 of crumbs to place on top before baking. Pour molasses mixture into crumbs. Blend well. Bake at 350° in ungreased pan, about 40 minutes. Enjoy!

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare apples at least 2 hours before baking.
Lay prepared drained apples in pie dish.
Combine first 3 ingredients in separate bowl; add beaten egg to form crumbs (if it doesn't crumb add another egg).
Top apples with crumbs and drizzle butter on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and cheese in a bowl.
Pour sausage-egg mixture into greased casserole dish. Stir and cover.
Bake at 375° until fully cooked.
Remove from oven; allow to cool.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cream ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Trim ends of squash, do not peel. Cook whole in boiling water for 5 minutes or till tender crisp.
Cool slightly and cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out pulp, leaving 1/4 inch thick shell.
Chop pulp, sprinkle shells lightly with salt. Arrange in a 2 quart rectangular baking dish.
In medium mixing bowl, combine egg, margarine, 1/4 c Parmesan cheese, onion, parsley and pepper.
Stir in pulp and bread crumbs.
Spoon filling into shells and sprinkle with the 1 Tbsp Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered in 350 degree oven for about 20 minutes or until set and heated through.
6 servings.

title: country fair shortbread cookies
directions: Note:
Can double recipe for approximately 8 dozen, depending on size.

title: pecan and coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in slow oven until firm.

title: custard pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pie shell.
Brush with egg white to prevent soaking.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt. Blend in milk, vanilla and butter.
Pour into shell; sprinkle on nutmeg.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 minutes, or until knife comes out clean.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together tomato soup, water or wine and flour until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients in covered roasting pan.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.
When ready to serve, adjust seasoning, if desired.
Serve over noodles or with crunchy French bread (to soak up gravy).

title: fluffy lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set aside. In a saucepan, combine gelatin, water and reserved juice. Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved. Refrigerate until syrupy, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar, sweet potato and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir flour mixture and nuts into egg mixture.
Mix in water.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a bowl.
Make a well; add all other ingredients.
Mix well until smooth.
Bake in a 350° oven in 3 well-greased and floured pans for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: marble cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing well, until blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, water and unsweetened chocolate in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in combined flour and sugar; add eggs, sour cream, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cut into squares.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; stir in okra.
Heat oil to 350°. Drop by tablespoons into oil.
Drain on paper towels; sprinkle with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix margarine, molasses, sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.
If dough is not stiff enough, add more flour.
Refrigerate dough several hours or overnight.
Make into small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Do not flatten.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Store in airtight container.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: In shallow dish or plastic bag, combine all ingredients except chicken; add chicken.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade; heat marinade thoroughly.
Grill or broil chicken, basting frequently with marinade.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, chocolate pudding, oil, eggs and water with wooden spoon.
Then add chocolate chips and sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir in as listed; pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls in jelly roll pan.
Whip the next 3 ingredients together and spread over the rolls.
Top with chopped up/shaved, fresh vegetables.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese together after it softens at room temperature.
Add the juice and sauce.
Whip thoroughly.
Form into a ball and roll in very finely chopped nuts.

title: smoky sausage 'n rice
directions: Cut sausage into bite size pieces.
Saute in oil.
Stir in onions and pepper.
Continue to saute until tender.
Stir in water, pimento, broth and black pepper. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice and peas.
Bring back to boil.
Cover.
Lower heat and simmer about 20 minutes. Makes six 1 cup servings.

title: apple phyllo triangles
directions: For filling, in a small mixing bowl, combine apple, raisins, sugar, flour, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Lightly brush 1 sheet of the phyllo dough with some of the melted margarine. Place another sheet of phyllo dough on top of the first sheet, then brush with margarine.
Top with the third sheet of phyllo. Do not brush with margarine.
Cut the stack of phyllo sheets lengthwise into four strips.

title: valentine's day creamy shrimp
directions: Place contents of shrimp soup and milk in a saucepan.
Heat slowly, stirring often, until sauce reaches boiling point and is smooth.
Add broken shrimp, drained.
Heat 5 minutes.
Serve over white rice tossed with pimiento.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Place orange juice and melted shortening in cup; add water to make 3/4 cup.
Add liquid to dry ingredients, then stir in egg.
Add berries and nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add egg, sour cream, flavoring and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add apples; mix thoroughly.
Pour into a pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and powdered sugar.
Add Rice Krispies, mixing lightly until well coated.
Use Pam spray and spread in cake pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: non-fat free peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
Roll batter into small balls.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheet.
With back of fork, press down on balls two times each to make a crisscross pattern. Place in oven at 350°.
Bake until done.

title: lemon baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together garlic, lemon peel and rosemary.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Mix lemon juice and water and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.
Turn over pieces every 20 to 25 minutes.
I don't cover the dish but think you could for most of the time.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce into pieces in bottom of large bowl.
Thinly slice and separate onion over lettuce.
Slice celery sticks and place over onions.
Drain chestnuts and place over celery.
Separate frozen peas and layer over celery.
Spread mayonnaise over peas, sealing at edge of bowl.
Sprinkle lemon-pepper and salt over mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar also.

title: gooey cinnamon rolls
directions: In a bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour.
Add milk, sugar, salt, butter, eggs and 1/2 of the flour to yeast.
Mix until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour to handle easily.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth, about 5 minutes. Round up in greased bowl.
Bring greased side up.
Cover with cloth.
Let rise until it doubles in size, about 1 1/2 hours.
Push down and let rise again until it is almost double, about 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oranges, juice, water and oil together for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
When ready to serve, add Fritos.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook beef; drain well.
Add onion to beef.
Cook until onion is slightly tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: In a small bowl, beat the eggs.
Add oil, vanilla and sugar. Sift flour, baking soda, salt, ground cinnamon and nutmeg into mixture.
Mix the 1/4 cup flour with apples, nuts and coconut. Then fold into mixture.
Batter will be very thick.
Spoon into greased 9-inch tube pan or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for approximately 70 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Whip cream cheese and vanilla until soft, about 5 minutes. Mix sugar and flour together so there are no lumps.
Slowly add cream cheese mixture to the sugar mixture.
Mix together eggs and cream.
Add to previous mixture.
Beat well.
Put into a pie pan that has a graham cracker crust.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar and flavoring.
Fold in broken Ritz crackers and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pie pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be served with whipped cream on top.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Pour hashbrowns into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over top of potato.
In saucepan, stir undiluted soup with cheese over low heat until melted.
Pour soup mixture over potato. Bake in 350° oven 40 to 60 minutes until browned.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken, crushing large tomato pieces.
Cover chicken with mixture and simmer for 30 minutes, covered, then 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered, until fork-tender. Serves 4.
About 330 calories per serving.

title: mexican casserole with velveeta
directions: Brown hamburger and drain fat.
Mix taco seasoning and let simmer.
In a medium saucepan, combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup, tomato sauce and Ro-Tel.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crush Doritos.
Then layer meat, onion and sauces.
Slice cheese and top.
Bake in 350° to 400° oven until cheese is melted.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Spray baking sheet with nonstick spray.
Place all ingredients in large bowl and use your hands to mix gently.
Shape turkey into a loaf and place on the baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Slice and serve with mashed potatoes and mushroom gravy.

title: french puffs
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add alternating with sour cream to butter mixture. Fold in dates or raisins.
Spoon into small muffin tins. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. While hot, roll puffs in 3/4 cup melted butter, then mixture of 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Makes 36.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonful or make into small balls and flatten a little.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in the warm water.
Add nuts, pineapple and pie filling.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and sugar until blended.
Spread over jello.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: angel kiss pie
directions: Butter a 9 to 10-inch pie plate.
Beat egg whites and salt stiff.
While beating, alternately and slowly add one cup of sugar and lemon juice.
Again, while beating, alternately and slowly add one cup of sugar and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 275° and 30 minutes at 300°.
Chill for a few hours or overnight.

title: hurry up home puffs
directions: Slicing lengthwise, cut 3 1/2-inch thick slices from the loaf of unsliced bread.
Toast the 3 slices on both sides.
Combine deviled ham and onion, then spread on toast, bringing right to edges.
Cut pimento in half.
Arrange 10 halves on each toast slice.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Combine mayonnaise, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Fold gently into beaten egg whites.
Spoon a mound of mixture over each olive slice.
Bake at 400° until golden, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cut each slice into 10 pieces.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: vegetable bites
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 tablespoon of melted butter.
Beat egg and water.
In separate bowl, mix flour and salt.
Dip 1/4 of vegetables into egg mixture. Remove one piece at a time and roll in flour mixture.
Place in greased pan.
Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Pour remaining melted butter over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, turning once, until vegetables are crisp-tender and golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 2 cups.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In
a
quart casserole, blend soup and milk; stir in tuna and
peas
or corn.
Top with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Yield:
3 or 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs. Combine flour and cocoa. Mix well. Stir in nuts. Bake at 350°.

title: chocolate mint ice cream pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream into the crust.
Freeze 1 to 2 hours.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Garnish with chocolate curls or fresh mint or drizzle with a little hot fudge.
Makes 8 servings.

title: boiled dressing
directions: Combine flour, granulated sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Break in the 2 eggs and mix thoroughly.
Dilute the vinegar with a little water and stir it in well.
Lastly, add milk. Place over boiling water and cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add the butter and stir until melted.
Add mustard and stir until dissolved.
Excellent served hot on hot salmon.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Mix ingredients and bring to a full boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 (12 ounce) package of semi-sweet chocolate morsels.
Stir until melted and smooth, then add 1/4 to 1/2 cup black walnuts, 1 teaspoon vanilla and about 1 cup of colored miniature marshmallows.
Do not overstir.
Spread into 8-inch square pan.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with liquid ingredients until well mixed and smooth. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350.

title: spinach pie(spanakopita)
directions: Wash spinach; cut off stems.
Boil 5 minutes, drain and squeeze out water.
Saute onion in olive oil, then add oil and onion to spinach, parsley, dill, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Cool and add eggs, Feta, Parmesan cheese and cottage cheese. Mix evenly.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and sweet milk well and add flour, salt, baking powder, melted margarine, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well and pour into 8-inch lightly greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until mixture sets.
It will make its own crust.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Reconstitute orange juice and lemonade according to directions. Mix all together and serve.

title: egg pies
directions: Bake at 350° to 400° for almost an hour.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil together water and sugar.
Mix orange juice.
Add to water and sugar mixture.
To this add strawberries, pineapple, peaches and bananas.
Freeze.
Let thaw slightly to serve slushy. This is great to take on picnics.

title: meringue
directions: Add the salt to the egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold the sugar gradually into them and add the flavoring.
Spread this meringue on the top of the filling and place in the oven at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons bacon grease.
Add beef, tomato paste, 3 tablespoons chili powder, garlic cloves, salt and pepper. Add water as needed.
Cook until well done.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Saute onion, mustard and ham.
Set aside to cool.
Butter 8-inch casserole dish.
Put half the bread on bottom and then add half the cheese.
Add ham mixture next.
Cover with remaining cheese and then bread cubes.
Beat eggs, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Cool.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Add flour mixture to shortening mixture; blend well.
Add date mixture.
Pour into greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with the sugar, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas sour cream
directions: Boil chicken; debone and chop in pieces.
Save the broth.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except the tortillas.
Cut tortillas in fourths and fold them into mixture.
Add enough broth to moisten and add flavor.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Place Swiss cheese on bottom of pie crust.
Sprinkle with broccoli, mushrooms and ham.
Blend next 4 ingredients in blender. Pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
4 to 6 servings.

title: vinaigrette
directions: Whisk all ingredients until oil and vinegar become creamy. Spoon onto salad as needed.

title: lemon tea
directions: For a light refreshing tea, add 1 can of frozen lemonade to a gallon of tea.
Refrigerate until cold before drinking.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 1 egg, and melted butter. Dough will be stiff. Spread into bottom of a 9 X 13 inch greased and floured pan. Then mix together remaining 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Pour over first layer and bake for 40-45 minutes at 325 degrees. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan heat first three ingredients until cranberry sauce is smooth.
Put chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Onions may be placed on and around chicken. Pour heated liquid mixture over chicken.
Cover dish with foil and bake for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: autumn cole slaw
directions: In a large bowl, mix cabbage, celery, apple and raisins.
Set aside.

title: party pate
directions: Melt butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion; saute until soft.
Make sure all cheeses and liverwurst are at room temperature.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Sift together the next 5 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Add apples; mix well. Stir in nuts and 1 cup morsels.
Spread batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining morsels over batter.
(Use a complete 12-ounce bag in cake.)
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: grand marnier cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch tube pan.
Line bottom with a circle of wax paper (in which a hole has been cut out at the center to accommodate the tube) and grease it.
Lightly dust bottom and sides with breadcrumbs and tap to remove excess.
Set aside.

title: sugar-free chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding as directed (minus 1/4 cup of milk).
Mix D-Zerta whipped topping as directed.
Pour pudding into pie crust.
Top with D-Zerta and chill overnight.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: *I use chicken breast quarters with bone.
Skin and rinse well.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place chicken and mushrooms over potatoes.
Stir together remaining ingredients except almonds and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: congealed cream cheese salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail juice (1 cup); add Jell-O and cool.
Add cream cheese, milk, mayonnaise, nuts and fruit cocktail.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini until half done. Saute onion in 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Mix well all ingredients, except crackers and rest of margarine.
Pour into buttered casserole bowl.
Top mixture with crackers and pour remaining margarine on top.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cook squash whole until done, boiling them.
Cut in half and remove the pulp, leaving the hull.
Mix other ingredients with the pulp.
Stuff into hulls and dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Serve warm.

title: cream soup mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use this recipe in place of "one can of cream of chicken soup":
mix 1/3 cup dry mix with 1 1/4 cups cold water in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
For cream of mushroom soup, add 1/2 small can mushrooms, chopped fine.
Use in casseroles or other recipes as you would the canned product.

title: grammy's american goulash
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and mix with 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yum-yum cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and eggs in large bowl. Mix well. Add the flour, oats, soda, baking powder and vanilla. Mix for about 3 minutes. Stir in coconut and nuts. Refrigerate for 1 hour. Dust hands with confectioners sugar and roll dough into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter with wire whisk.
Stir in honey.
Cover; store in refrigerator.
Serve with hot muffins or biscuits.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle in a layer each of graham cracker crumbs, chocolate pieces, coconut and nuts.
Pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: brown sugar apple pie
directions: Grease pie plate, peel and slice apples, layer in pie plate, sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Dot with butter.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup flour.
Arrange this mixture in flattened dabs or crumble on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are soft.

title: lasagna
directions: Blend (not too much) pepper, celery, onion, garlic, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Salt and pepper ground beef in deep skillet and brown.
Add blended tomato mixture.
Add mushrooms and other spices, a little at a time to taste.
Let simmer until thickens slightly.
Boil lasagna noodles in salted (1 teaspoon) water, adding bouillon cube.
When noodles are soft, drain.
Begin layering in large deep casserole dish, 1 layer of lasagna sauce from skillet, 1 layer of noodles, 2 slices of Mozzarella cheese and 1 tub of cottage cheese.
Repeat, ending with a final layer of lasagna sauce on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cream together the next 3 ingredients. Pour over the first layer; sprinkle nuts on the top.
Press nuts into the mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: pink stuff
directions: Grind the cranberries in food processor. Place in plastic or glass container with sugar or Equal. Stir well and refrigerate overnight or all day. Drain the pineapple and fold into cranberries. Add pecans. Fold all into the Cool Whip. Chill. Serve anytime of year or at your holiday get-togethers.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all the ingredients together.
Oil pan lightly (9 x 9-inch).
Pour into baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes, until set and lightly brown.
Cool and cut into tiny squares for appetizer or large squares for side dish.
Freezes very well.

title: saunder's frosting
directions: Mix all together and beat until stiff.

title: nacho pizza
directions: Place nachos on cookie sheet.
Cook ground beef, chilli mix and taco mix and cook until beef is cooked.
Pour over nachos. Add salsa sauce, green pepper, onion, Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and roll in chopped pecans.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Pour boiling water over the chocolate; let stand until cool. Cream the butter and vanilla.
Add brown sugar and add eggs one at a time.
Mix together the flour, soda and salt.
Stir this into creamed mixture; mix well.
Blend in sour cream and chocolate water.
Bake in prepared loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sandwich nut cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together on a floured board. Add sifted flour and eggs.
Mix well. Roll cookie dough on board. Cut with round cookie cutter.

Place half of the rounds on lightly greased baking sheet. The other half of the rounds should be cut out of the center with smaller round cutter. Dip the centered halves into egg white and then ground nuts.
Place on baking sheet. Bake 12 minutes.
Spread bottom portion with jams or preserves, then add center cut cookie to top.
Makes about 48 cookies.
Very attractive and delicious.

title: cantonese style stir-fried eggs
directions: Mix shrimp, pea pods, bean sprouts, bok choy and mushrooms in a large bowl.
Add eggs, soy sauce, salt, pepper and sesame oil to shrimp and vegetables; mix well.
Heat cooking oil in wok or large skillet.
Pour in egg mixture and spread to cover the bottom of the wok or skillet.
Turn egg over as soon as it settles.
Cook the mixture until it is firm.
Dish out onto platter and serve.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and put into graham cracker crust.
Let stand 24 hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Pour melted margarine over flour and nuts.
Mix good and spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar a little at a time and cream together well, then add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each one.
Then add flour alternately with milk, beating well each time.
Add salt and flavorings.
Put cake in tube pan in a cold oven.
Turn to 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, then cut cake and let it stay in for 20 more minutes, then take out.

title: bear stew
directions: Brown meat well in hot fat.
Season with salt and pepper. Cover with hot water and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add cubed vegetables and bay leaves, and cook slowly 25 minutes.
When meat and vegetables are tender, thicken slightly with flour mixed with cold water.

title: pink christmas salad
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, salad dressing, sugar, cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place paper baking cups in muffin pans.
Fill with salad mixture. Freeze.
When frozen, remove from muffin pans and store in plastic bags (or freezer containers) in freezer.
Serve frozen or very slightly thawed.
